ence-doesnt-predict-a-new-hires-success%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earen't%20always%20good%20predictors%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20who%20will%20succeed%20in%20a%20role.%20And%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20can%20leave%20candidates%20exposed%20to%20bias%20in%20the%20hiring%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221645%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Khyati%20Sundaram%2C%20CEO%20of%20Applied%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e209876080194819fba5b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221097%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKhyati%20Sundaram%2C%20CEO%20of%20Applied.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Applied%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20for%20all%20the%20frustration%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Fim-recruiter-i-hate-resumes-mark-jensen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20need%20to%20tinker%20with%20them%20to%20make%20it%20past%20seemingly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatgpt-hiring-ghost-interviews-job-search-weird-labor-market-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpenetrable%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20employers%20use%20to%20sift%20through%20applicants%2C%20there's%20likely%20little%20chance%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0for%20now%2C%20at%20least%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20will%20go%20the%20way%20of%20paper%20paychecks.%20But%20a%20move%20toward%20screening%20for%20skills%20could%2C%20advocates%20hope%2C%20result%20in%20a%20demotion%20for%20the%20CV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShow%20us%20what%20you%20can%20do%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20buzzy%20idea%20floating%20around%20HR%20departments%20is%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bskills-based%20hiring.%26quot%3B%20It%20would%20have%20employers%20focus%20on%20a%20candidate's%20abilities%20and%20less%20on%20traditional%20qualifications%20like%20college%20degrees%20or%20formal%20experience%20in%20a%20role.%20One%20way%20to%20measure%20skills%20is%20to%20do%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.beapplied.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApplied%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20companies%20do%3A%20have%20you%20take%20a%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESundaram%20said%20the%20approach%20of%20testing%20can%20help%20make%20hiring%20fairer.%20The%20company%20might%20use%20only%20five%20or%20six%20questions%20per%20test%20to%20help%20identify%20suitable%20job%20candidates.%20In%20a%20statistical%20analysis%2C%20Applied%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.beapplied.com%2Fpost%2Fcan-we-predict-applicant-performance-without-requiring-cvs-putting-applied-to-the-test-part-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E60%25%20of%20the%20approximately%2025%2C000%20hires%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20through%20its%20platform%20would%20have%20been%20overlooked%20based%20on%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20small%20study%2C%20the%20approach%20resulted%20in%20two-thirds%20more%20women%20getting%20into%20STEM%20roles.%20And%2C%20in%20another%20larger%20review%2C%20Black%20candidates%20getting%20jobs%20in%20finance%20and%20consulting%20increased%20by%20nearly%2080%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20employers%20do%20want%20to%20see%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20Applied%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20strip%20away%20information%20about%20gender%20and%20ethnicity.%20That%20makes%20it%20more%20likely%20a%20variety%20of%20candidates%20will%20get%20a%20look%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinding%20candidates%20who%20don't%20look%20the%20part%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApplied%20isn't%20alone%20in%20seeing%20tests%20as%20a%20better%20way%20to%20identify%20the%20best%20candidates.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shl.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESHL%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20global%20talent%20screening%20company%2C%20offers%20a%2015-minute%20assessment%20that%20employers%20can%20give%20to%20job%20seekers.%20The%20test%20measures%2096%20soft%20skills%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0things%20like%20how%20someone%20communicates%20or%20how%20consultative%20or%20persuasive%20a%20candidate%20is.%20SHL%20has%20also%20developed%20hundreds%20of%20tests%20that%20examine%20specific%20business%20and%20technical%20abilities%2C%20including%20coding%20simulations%20in%20more%20than%2050%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarlene%20Dunne%2C%20chief%20talent%20advisor%20at%20SHL%20Americas%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20assessments%20are%20consistent%20across%20candidates%20and%20are%20designed%20to%20be%20relevant%20to%20a%20job.%20The%20tests%20can%20help%20identify%20candidates%20who%20might%20not%20have%20certain%20experience%20listed%20on%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20but%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrganizations%20are%20willing%20to%20place%20bets%20on%20people%20where%20they%20feel%20like%20they%20at%20least%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20demonstrate%20or%20be%20aligned%20to%20some%20of%20the%20skills%20that%20they%20need%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20haven't%20had%20work%20experience%20around%20those%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Dunne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFocusing%20on%20the%20results%20of%20an%20assessment%20rather%20than%20a%20candidate's%20pedigree%20can%20make%20it%20less%20likely%20those%20hiring%20will%20make%20assumptions%20based%20on%20things%20like%20where%20a%20person%20might%20have%20gone%20to%20school%2C%20Dunne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20found%20that%20when%20indications%20of%20gender%20or%20ethnicity%20are%20stripped%20from%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20people%20from%20various%20backgrounds%20get%20a%20better%20shot%20at%20landing%20a%20job.%20That%20can%20make%20it%20more%20likely%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-help-recruit-hire-employees-tech-women-bias-job-seeking-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20will%20find%20jobs%20in%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeploying%20tests%20early%20in%20the%20process%20can%20help%20ensure%20people%20getting%20interviews%20aren't%20wasting%20anyone's%20time%2C%20Dunne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOftentimes%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20man%20hours%20that%20get%20eaten%20up%20interviewing%20people%20that%20really%20shouldn't%20be%20getting%20interviewed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20test%20might%20be%20a%20turn-off%20for%20some%20candidates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAaron%20Cleavinger%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Murdoch%20Mason%20Executive%20Search%20Group%2C%20told%20BI%20he's%20often%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20testing%20applicants%C2%A0because%20he%20doesn't%20see%20assessments%20as%20good%20predictors%20of%20someone's%20success%20in%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECleavinger%20added%20that%20tests%20or%20tasks%20can%20turn%20off%20top-tier%20workers%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20bothered.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20anger%20the%20most%20qualified%20candidate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Tests%20can%20be%20appropriate%2C%20Cleavinger%20said%2C%20when%20a%20role%20depends%20largely%20on%20how%20well%20someone%20can%20complete%20a%20particular%20technical%20task%20on%20a%20computer%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20sees%20value%20in%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20artifact%20you%20leave%20behind.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20way%20for%20an%20interviewer%20to%20remember%20what%20stood%20out%20about%20a%20candidate%2C%20Cleavinger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20for%20the%20world%20where%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20no%20longer%20needed%2C%20and%20you%20can%20simply%20and%20easily%20assess%20candidates%20based%20on%20their%20capability%20and%20qualifications%20for%20a%20role%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20doesn't%20expect%20we'll%20soon%20be%20able%20to%20ditch%20our%20CVs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20her%20part%2C%20Sundaram%20expects%20AI%20will%20change%20how%20so%20many%20people%20work%20that%20job%20candidates'%20employment%20histories%20might%20often%20reflect%20a%20smorgasbord%20of%20experiences.%20That%20means%20detecting%20workers'%20abilities%2C%20not%20just%20what%20they've%20done%2C%20will%20be%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20hit%20us%20in%20the%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20divide%20at%20one%20point%20will%20be%20there%20are%20so%20many%20jobs%20out%20there%20that%20the%20job%20description%20%E2%80%94%20the%20skills%20required%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0do%20not%20match%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20that%20exist%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-tests-impact-on-resume-and-employment-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709467081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e209a7ce7f1785b2e5621a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-tests-impact-on-resume-and-employment-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Khyati%20Sundaram%2C%20CEO%20at%20Applied%2C%20is%20pushing%20for%20skills-based%20hiring%20over%20traditional%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20aiming%20to%20reduce%20bias%20and%20improve%20job%20matching.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-tests-impact-on-resume-and-employment-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Noida%20Mall%20Trip%20Turns%20Fatal%20For%202%20After%20Iron%20Grille%20Falls%20On%20Them%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Sunday%20mall%20trip%20turned%20fatal%20for%20two%20men%20from%20Ghaziabad%20when%20an%20iron%20grille%20crushed%20them%20at%20Greater%20Noida's%20Blue%20Sapphire%20Mall%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20senior%20police%20officer%20Hridesh%20Katheria%2C%20Harendra%20and%20Shakeel%20were%20walking%20t