F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Turns%20out%20sports%20gambling%20was%20a%20gateway%20drug%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hand%20holding%20a%20smartphone%20with%20falling%20casino%20chips%2C%20playing%20cards%2C%20and%20money%2C%20symbolizing%20sports%20betting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e2063b6080194819fba36a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESports%20betting%20apps%20are%20betting%20that%20Americans%20want%20to%20gamble%20on%20more%20than%20just%20sports.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDraftKings%20would%20love%20it%20if%20you%20bet%20on%20the%20Knicks%20game.%20Oh%2C%20and%20while%20you're%20at%20it%2C%20why%20don't%20you%20hop%20over%20to%20its%20casino%20app%20and%20try%20out%20a%20little%20online%20blackjack%3F%20And%20wouldn't%20it%20be%20neat%20to%20eventually%20toss%20a%20few%20bucks%20on%20some%20lottery%20tickets%2C%20too%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20more%20and%20more%20Americans%20are%20getting%20used%20to%20wagering%20on%20games%20from%20their%20phone%2C%20sports%20betting%20is%20just%20the%20start.%20The%20next%20step%20is%20to%20get%20people%20to%20gamble%20on%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESports%20betting%20has%20exploded%20since%202018%2C%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20down%20a%20federal%20law%20prohibiting%20it.%20Thirty-eight%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20have%20legalized%20wagering%2C%20and%20sports%20leagues%2C%20which%20once%20shunned%20even%20the%20faintest%20idea%20of%20betting%20on%20their%20games%2C%20have%20embraced%20it.%20Even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-ceo-sports-gambling-betting-wont-hurt-family-brand-espn-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDisney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20bastion%20of%20family%20friendliness%2C%20is%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20pie.%20And%20it's%20quite%20a%20big%20pie%3A%20Americans%20legally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americangaming.org%2Fresources%2Faga-commercial-gaming-revenue-tracker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebet%3C%2Fa%3E%20%24119.84%20billion%20on%20sports%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Gaming%20Association%2C%20a%2027.8%25%20increase%20from%202022.%20Sports-betting%20revenue%20hit%20%2410.92%20billion%20last%20year%2C%20up%2044.5%25.%20While%20growth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fmarketintelligence%2Fen%2Fnews-insights%2Flatest-news-headlines%2Famerican-gaming-association-legal-sports-betting-hits-record-revenue-in-2023-80522087%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emay%20not%20continue%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20as%20high%20of%20a%20pace%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20many%20more%20states%20will%20legalize%20sports%20betting%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20obvious%20that%20betting%20isn't%20slowing%20down.%20The%20industry%20expects%20activity%20to%20keep%20picking%20up%20in%20the%20states%20that%20have%20already%20greenlighted%20it.%20The%20American%20Gaming%20Association%20estimates%20bettors%20wagered%20%2423.1%20billion%20on%20this%20year's%20Super%20Bowl%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20online-gambling%20companies%20don't%20plan%20to%20stick%20to%20just%20sports.%20The%20bigger-picture%20bet%20is%20that%20once%20someone%20gambles%20on%20an%20NBA%20or%20NFL%20game%2C%20they'll%20develop%20a%20taste%20for%20gambling%20on%20other%20things%2C%20too.%20That%20will%20give%20companies%20more%20avenues%20to%20dip%20into%20consumers'%20wallets%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20more%20lucrative%20than%20sports%20betting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20companies%20do%20not%20make%20anywhere%20near%20as%20much%20money%20off%20sports%20wagering%20as%20they%20do%20with%20online%20casinos%2C%20but%20they%20do%20get%20their%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20with%20the%20sports%20wagering%2C%26quot%3B%20Lia%20Nower%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Gambling%20Studies%20at%20Rutgers%20University%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20DraftKings%3A%20The%20Boston-based%20sports-entertainment%20and%20gaming%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdraftkings.gcs-web.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fnews-release-details%2Fdraftkings-reaches-agreement-acquire-jackpocket-750-million%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20it%20was%20buying%20Jackpocket%2C%20an%20app%20that%20lets%20people%20buy%20lottery%20tickets%20online%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20proposed%20%24750%20million%20deal.%20DraftKings%20also%20has%20an%20online-casino%20app%20and%20bought%20Golden%20Nugget%20Online%20Gaming%20in%202022%20as%20part%20of%20its%20effort%20to%20build%20out%20its%20iGaming%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20think%20online%20blackjack%2C%20roulette%2C%20and%20slot%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20DraftKings%20CEO%20Jason%20Robins%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casino.org%2Fnews%2Fdraftkings-ceo-sees-big-igaming-growth-ahead%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20iGaming%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20chunk%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20company's%20revenues%20already%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bhidden%20gem%26quot%3B%20for%20DraftKings.%20In%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdraftkings.gcs-web.com%2Fevents%2Fevent-details%2Fdraftkings-q4-2023-earnings-call%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20recent%20earnings%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Robins%20talked%20about%20the%20overlap%20between%20DraftKings%20customers%20and%20Jackpocket%20customers%20and%20touted%20the%20cross-selling%20opportunities%20he%20saw%20for%20all%20of%20DraftKings'%20products.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20all%20sorts%20of%20different%20levers%20that%20you%20can%20pull%2C%20and%20the%20important%20thing%20is%20not%20to%20force%20anything%2C%20to%20try%20to%20just%20get%20the%20right%20products%20in%20front%20of%20the%20right%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDraftKings%20isn't%20alone.%20FanDuel%2C%20which%20is%20owned%20by%20Flutter%2C%20a%20Dublin-based%20sports-betting%20and%20iGaming%20company%2C%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casino.org%2Fnews%2Ffanduel-focusing-on-igaming-improvements%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20on%20building%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20iGaming%20offering.%20Caesars%20and%20MGM%2C%20both%20of%20which%20have%20sports-betting%20arms%2C%20are%20hopping%20on%20the%20iGaming%20train%2C%20too%2C%20though%20it's%20a%20delicate%20dance%20for%20the%20casino%20stalwarts%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20cannibalize%20their%20brick-and-mortar%20operations%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20iGaming%20is%20legal%20in%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20states%20%E2%80%94%20New%20Jersey%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20Delaware%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Rhode%20Island%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20West%20Virginia%20%E2%80%94%20while%20there's%20legislation%20pending%20in%20other%20places%2C%20including%20New%20York.%20As%20the%20prevalence%20of%20online%20betting%20grows%2C%20there's%20plenty%20of%20revenue%20to%20be%20had.%20Chad%20Beynon%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Macquarie%2C%20laid%20out%20some%20of%20the%20calculations%20driving%20these%20investments.%20The%20average%20sports%20bettor%20may%20spend%20about%20%241%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20the%20average%20person%20doing%20iGaming%20could%20spend%20%245%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20the%20action%20is%2024%2F7%2C%20while%20there's%20a%20finite%20number%20of%20sports%20games%20to%20bet%20on.%20And%20then%20there's%20the%20lottery%2C%20where%20an%20average%20player%20will%20spend%20%24300%20a%20year.%20All%20that%20combined%20under%20one%20umbrella%20translates%20to%20dollar%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSports%20betting%20is%20kind%20of%20like%20the%20customer-acquisition%20channel%2C%20and%20then%20you%20cross-sell%20them%20other%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Benyon%20said.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20they're%20trying%20to%20be%20digital%20leaders%2C%20and%20whether%20it's%20lottery%20tickets%2C%20sports%20betting%2C%20I%20think%20these%20companies%20ultimately%20want%20to%20do%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drive%20into%20iGaming%20is%20particularly%20appealing%20because%20sports%20betting%20is%20a%20low-margin%20business.%20Companies%20have%20to%20pay%20leagues%20or%20third-party%20vendors%20for%20data%20and%20wait%20for%20games%20to%20happen.%20By%20contrast%2C%20online%20tables%20are%20open%20all%20year%2C%20around%20the%20clock%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20one%20to%20pay%20to%20host%20the%20action.%20Plus%2C%20Nower%20told%20me%2C%20the%20payouts%20on%20games%20such%20as%20slots%20or%20roulette%20are%20much%20more%20favorable%20to%20the%20operator%20than%20sports%20betting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESports%20betting%20can%20also%20help%20to%20solve%20an%20age-old%20problem%20for%20casinos%20and%20other%20traditional%20forms%20of%20gambling%3A%20getting%20younger%20people%20hooked.%20A%2022-year-old%20may%20not%20go%20to%20Atlantic%20City%20to%20hit%20up%20the%20blackjack%20table%2C%20but%20they'll%20make%20a%20prop%20bet%20on%20a%20baseball%20game%20on%20their%20phone%20and%20maybe%20try%20out%20a%20few%20hands%20of%20blackjack%20while%20they%20wait%20for%20the%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20finding%20is%20since%20the%20legalization%20of%20online%20casino%20gaming%20and%20sports%20wagering%2C%20more%20people%20are%20wagering%20online%20and%20more%20people%20are%20wagering%20both%20in%20land-based%20and%20online%20venues%2C%26quot%3B%20Nower%20said%2C%20citing%20a%20recent%20report%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsocialwork.rutgers.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FPrevalence_Report_2023_Final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprevalence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20gambling%20in%20New%20Jersey%20she%20coauthored.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20this%20additive%20effect%20of%20more%20forms%20of%20gambling%20that%20are%20legalized%20and%20more%20ways%20in%20which%20you%20can%20gamble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESports-betting%20companies%20want%20to%20not%20only%20break%20into%20people's%20gambling%20budgets%20but%20also%20get%20into%20their%20entertainment%20budgets%2C%20said%20Chris%20Grove%2C%20a%20sports-gambling-industry%20investor%20at%20Acies%20Investments%20and%20a%20partner%20at%20EKG%20Ventures%2C%20which%20invested%20in%20Jackpocket.%20These%20companies%20could%20start%20to%20offer%20products%20that%20may%20%3Cem%3Ebe%3C%2Fem%3E%20gambling%20but%20not%20%3Cem%3Efeel%3C%2Fem%3E%20like%20it%20to%20consumers%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20didn't%20really%20think%20of%20the%20lottery%20as%20gambling%2C%20even%20though%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20companies%2C%20DraftKings%2C%20FanDuel%2C%20etc.%2C%20is%20to%20really%20ask%20the%20question%20of%2C%20yes%2C%20I%20can%20try%20to%20win%20more%20share%20of%20that%20gambling%20dollar%2C%20gambling%20budget%2C%20but%20that%20really%20only%20goes%20so%20far%2C%20and%20it%20gets%20more%20and%20more%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20greater%20my%20share%20becomes%2C%20I%20need%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20how%20I%20can%20access%20the%20broader%20entertainment%20share%20of%20the%20consumer%20wallet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20dissimilar%20to%20what%20Las%20Vegas%20has%20done%20over%20the%20years%2C%20Grove%20said.%20It's%20a%20destination%20for%20not%20just%20gambling%20but%20also%20shows%20and%20hotels%20and%2C%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-who-created-las-vegas-sphere-venetian-concert-arena-photos-inside%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Sphere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Play%20it%20forward%2C%20and%20what%20this%20looks%20like%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20could%20be%20an%20ecosystem%20of%20brands%20and%20products%2C%20some%20of%20which%20look%20very%20much%20like%20gambling%2C%20some%20of%20which%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20as%20fun%20as%20sports%20gambling%20is%20%E2%80%94%20as%20is%20gambling%20in%20general%20%E2%80%94%20it%20has%20some%20serious%20downsides%20for%20society.%20Sportsbooks%20and%20gambling%20operations%20say%20they're%20a%20meaningful%20source%20of%20tax%20revenue%20for%20states%2C%20which%20is%20why%20states%20greenlight%20them%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20That's%20true%2C%20though%20just%20how%20much%20money%20is%20being%20raised%20can%20really%20vary%20from%20state%20to%20state.%20There's%20also%20the%20question%20of%20trade-offs.%20Gambling%20addiction%20is%20a%20real%20problem%20that%20often%20gets%20glossed%20over.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncpgambling.org%2Fhelp-treatment%2Ffaqs-what-is-problem-gambling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Council%20on%20Problem%20Gambling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202%20million%20Americans%20have%20a%20severe%20gambling%20problem%2C%20and%20another%204%20million%20to%206%20million%20a%20mild%20or%20moderate%20problem.%20As%20depicted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DwXZNuwY_5-U%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20%26quot%3BSNL%26quot%3B%20skit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20gist%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20sports-betting%20ads%20is%20basically%2C%20%26quot%3BSPORTS%20BETTING%20IS%20COOL%20AND%20GREAT%20AND%20AWESOME%20(and%20also%20here's%20a%20number%20for%20if%20you%20have%20a%20problem%2C%20but%20let's%20not%20think%20too%20hard%20about%20that).%26quot%3B%20What%20gambling%20companies%20will%20note%20is%20that%20they%20have%20a%20number%20of%20consumer%20protections%20in%20place%20that%20illegal%20and%20offshore%20operations%20don't%20%E2%80%94%20cooling-off%20periods%2C%20mechanisms%20for%20gamblers%20to%20set%20limits%20on%20things%20including%20their%20deposits%20and%20wagers%2C%20and%20tools%20to%20automatically%20detect%20potential%20problem%20gambling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpanding%20the%20offerings%20means%20greater%20risk%20of%20more%20people%20developing%20an%20unhealthy%20gambling%20habit.%20In%20New%20York%2C%20calls%20to%20problem-gambling%20hotlines%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osc.ny.gov%2Fpress%2Freleases%2F2023%2F10%2Fdinapoli-mobile-sports-betting-adds-state-revenue-calls-problem-gambling-hotline-rise-gaming%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWith%2520the%2520legalization%2520of%2520mobile%2COASAS)%2520from%25202021%2520to%25202022.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20increased%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20with%20the%20tax%20revenue%20the%20state%20makes%20off%20sports%20betting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20online%20space%2C%20which%20is%2024%20hours%20a%20day%20and%20in%20your%20pocket%2C%20is%20driving%20more%20involvement%2C%26quot%3B%20Nower%20said.%20The%20more%20people%20gamble%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20more%20culturally%20acceptable%20gambling%20becomes%20%E2%80%94%20the%20more%20possibility%20gambling%20addiction%20becomes%20a%20bigger%20issue.%20It%20also%20depends%20how%20many%20states%20get%20on%20board%20with%20iGaming%2C%20which%20they've%20generally%20been%20more%20wary%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20culture%20around%20gambling%20in%20America%20has%20meaningfully%20shifted%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20in%20no%20small%20part%20because%20of%20sports%20betting.%20I%20partake%2C%20though%20not%20heavily%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20been%20betting%20the%20same%20%2420%20up%20and%20down%20on%20the%20Caesars%20app%20for%20over%20a%20year.%20If%20New%20York%20legalizes%20iGaming%2C%20might%20I%20start%20doing%20slots%20on%20my%20phone%3F%20Personally%2C%20I%20don't%20know.%20But%20companies%20are%20betting%20many%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20t