.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20grow%20up%20in%20a%20small%20town%20like%20Sonoma%2C%20in%20a%20notorious%20family%20business%20where%20everybody%20knows%20who%20you%20are%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20important%20to%20me%20to%20carve%20my%20own%20path%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20path%20led%20to%20snacks.%20In%202009%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20offerings%20at%20a%20local%20butcher%20shop%2C%20Sebastiani%20founded%20an%20upscale%20beef-jerky%20business%20called%20Krave.%20Easier%20to%20chew%20and%20sweeter%20than%20convenience-store%20jerky%2C%20Krave%20got%20huge%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-rise-of-the-meat-protein-bar-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20paleo%20craze%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202015%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkrave-jerky-and-hershey-2015-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESebastiani%20sold%20the%20company%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Hershey%2C%20the%20chocolate-bar%20people%2C%20for%20%24240%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20ran%20the%20company%20for%20Hershey%20for%20a%20year%2C%20then%20left%20to%20found%20a%20food-focused%20investment%20firm.%20But%20Krave%20had%20been%20more%20than%20a%20financial%20success.%20It%20created%20a%20whole%20new%20category%20in%20the%20snack%20industry.%20And%20Sebastiani%20found%20himself%20jonesing%20for%20that%20high.%20In%20search%20of%20it%2C%20he%20went%20to%20Paris.%20There%20%E2%80%94%20in%20cute%20bakeries%2C%20in%20nice%20shops%2C%20on%20haute%20dessert%20menus%20%E2%80%94%20he%20discovered%20next-level%20marshmallows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20weren't%20the%20pot-bellied%2C%20chemical-laden%20puffballs%20that%20Americans%20roast%20on%20sticks%20and%20slap%20on%20s'mores.%20They%20were%20toothsome%20little%20pastel-shaded%20cubes%2C%20in%20a%20range%20of%20classy%20flavors%20that%20called%20to%20mind%20meringues%20and%20Michelin%20stars.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20peel%20back%20the%20layers%20of%20a%20marshmallow%2C%20it's%20actually%20a%20better%20product%20for%20you%2C%20with%20less%20sugar%2C%20than%20most%20candies%2C%26quot%3B%20Sebastiani%20realized.%20%26quot%3BWe%20could%20be%20a%20less-guilty%2C%20better-for-you%20sweet%20indulgence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%3A%20Create%20a%20premium%20snack%20by%20using%20(nominally)%20healthier%20ingredients%20than%20commodity%20marshmallows%20and%20smashing%20together%20flavors%20and%20colors%20inspired%20by%20Paris.%20That%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20the%20source%20of%20the%20new%20company's%20name%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fsmashmallow-healthy-gourmet-marshmallow-review-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESmashmallow%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20say%20it%20was%20the%20Krave%20playbook%2C%26quot%3B%20Sebastiani%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20was%20my%20next%20concept%20that%20I%20believed%20was%20going%20to%20disrupt%20a%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20you've%20heard%20of%20Smashmallow%3B%20maybe%20you%20even%20bought%20some.%20In%20the%20couple%20of%20years%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20they%20were%20everywhere.%20Now%3F%20%3Cem%3EPfft%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20problem%20wasn't%20the%20marshmallows%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%2C%20by%20all%20accounts%2C%20delicious.%20The%20problem%20was%20scale.%20Smashmallows%20were%20designed%20to%20look%20like%20an%20artisanal%2C%20boutique%20product%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20enough%20for%20Sebastiani%3A%20He%20wanted%20to%20manufacture%20%3Cem%3Ebillions%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20them%2C%20to%20build%20a%20company%20that%20would%20bestride%20Candyland%20like%20a%20squishy%20colossus.%20That%20meant%20he%20had%20to%20grow%20fast%20and%20figure%20out%20the%20engineering%20on%20the%20fly%20%E2%80%94%20the%20classic%20entrepreneurial%20strategy%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%20When%20it%20works%2C%20you%20get%20Tesla%3B%20when%20it%20doesn't%2C%20you%20get%20Theranos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20story%20of%20the%20Theranos%20of%20marshmallows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222131%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Square%20shape%20marshmallows%20falling%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c15b6b7a3d27148877e4b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223983%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELiam%20Eisenberg%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20their%20denser%20cousins%20nougat%20and%20taffy%2C%20marshmallows%20are%2C%20formally%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1007%2F978-3-319-61742-8_11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaerated%20confections%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Dissolve%20sugar%20in%20water%20with%20a%20goo-like%20gelatin%20or%20egg%20white%2C%20then%20whip%20until%20tiny%20bubbles%20form.%20The%20gelatin%20locks%20the%20bubbles%20in%20place.%20Cook%20it%20gently%20and%20you%20get%20an%20airy%20bite%20of%20sweetness%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%26quot%3Bfoam%20made%20of%20finely%20dispersed%20air%20bubbles%20within%20a%20sugar%20candy%20matrix%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20one%20candymaking%20textbook%20puts%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20hard%20to%20make%20a%20better%20version%20of%20store-bought%20marshmallows.%20Jens%20Hoj%2C%20a%20former%20chef%20at%20the%20renowned%20restaurant%20Chez%20Panisse%2C%20had%20figured%20out%20the%20cooking%20process%20that%20turned%20Krave%20into%20a%20giant%20of%20the%20jerky%20world.%20He%20was%20confident%20he%20could%20do%20the%20same%20for%20Smashmallow.%20%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20a%20marshmallow%20to%20have%20a%20little%20bite%20to%20it%2C%20not%20just%20be%20a%20foamy%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20First%2C%20he%20replaced%20the%20corn%20syrup%20in%20commercial%20marshmallows%20with%20tapioca%20syrup%20and%20invert%20sugar.%20Then%20he%20cooked%20the%20mixture%20at%20a%20slightly%20higher%20temperature%2C%20to%20give%20the%20marshmallow%20more%20texture%20than%20the%20basic%20Kraft%20offering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20only%20a%20few%20months%20to%20get%20all%20that%20right.%20But%20then%20Hoj%20ran%20into%20a%20problem.%20He%20couldn't%20find%20anyone%20to%20make%20his%20marshmallow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20when%20someone%20turns%20a%20food%20into%20a%20business%20%E2%80%94%20mom's%20chili%2C%20auntie's%20kimchi%2C%20whatever%20%E2%80%94%20they%20end%20up%20moving%20to%20an%20industrial-scale%20facility%20called%20a%20copacker.%20Copackers%20for%20meat%20are%20common%3B%20finding%20them%20for%20Krave%20had%20been%20simple.%20Locating%20one%20that%20could%20handle%20a%20delicate%2C%20airy%20confection%20proved%20a%20whole%20lot%20tougher.%20Which%2C%20in%20retrospect%2C%20should%20have%20served%20as%20a%20warning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoj's%20team%20eventually%20found%20a%20commercial%20bakery%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20that%20was%20willing%20to%20learn.%20Smashmallow%20bought%20big%2C%20commercial%20Hobart%20mixers%20to%20combine%20and%20whip%20the%20sugar%20and%20gelatin.%20They%20poured%20the%20mix%20onto%20huge%20cookie%20sheets%2C%20on%20top%20of%20starch%20to%20keep%20it%20from%20sticking%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20called%20%26quot%3Bslabbing.%26quot%3B%20They%20bought%20special%20cutters%20to%20slice%20the%20hardened%20marshmallow%20into%20cubes%2C%20and%20learned%20how%20to%20dust%20them%20with%20sugar%20and%20cinnamon%20to%20make%20a%20churro%20flavor%2C%20to%20blend%20in%20other%20flavors%20like%20strawberry%20and%20root%20beer%2C%20to%20include%20chocolate%20chips%20or%20coconut%20flakes%2C%20to%20pour%20out%20multiple%20layers%20to%20get%20two-color%20versions.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20all%20hand-done%2C%20so%20it%20was%20extremely%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20%26quot%3BImagine%2030%20people%20making%20marshmallows%20every%20day%2C%20seven%20days%20a%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESebastiani%20had%20the%20contacts%20to%20get%20the%20product%20into%20stores%2C%20where%20it%20proved%20even%20more%20popular%20than%20he'd%20hoped.%20%26quot%3BThis%20wasn't%20a%20novelty%20purchase%20where%20they%20go%20'Oh%2C%20that's%20cute'%20and%20then%20never%20buy%20it%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Sebastiani%20says.%20%26quot%3BCustomers%20were%20actually%20buying%20it%20and%20then%20buying%20it%20again%20in%20different%20flavors.%20Retailers%20were%20clamoring%20for%20more%20seasonality%2C%20for%20smaller%20packages%20so%20moms%20could%20buy%20it%20for%20grab-and-go%20for%20their%20kids'%20lunchboxes.%26quot%3B%20It%20had%20taken%20Krave%20five%20years%20to%20reach%20%245%20million%20in%20annual%20revenue.%20Smashmallow%20got%20to%20%245%20million%20in%20its%20first%20year.%20The%20next%20year%2C%20its%20revenue%20doubled.%20Retailers%20like%20Target%20and%20Walmart%20were%20clamoring%20for%20more%2C%20and%20Sebastiani%20was%20bringing%20outside%20investors%20on%20board.%20%26quot%3BWe%20got%20extra%20excited%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20weren't%20just%20premium.%20We%20were%20%E2%80%94%20I%20call%20it%20a%20%3Cem%3Eusage%20occasion%20disruption%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmashmallow%20had%20a%20killer%20brand%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20product%20was%20still%20basically%20being%20made%20one%20batch%20at%20a%20time%2C%20on%20kitchen%20counters.%20To%20automate%20the%20assembly%20line%2C%20Hoj%20knew%20they'd%20need%20to%20switch%20from%20slabbing%20the%20marshmallows%20on%20cookie%20sheets%20to%20%26quot%3Bextrusion%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20conveyor-belt%20process%20used%20for%20mass-produced%20marshmallows.%20Extrusion%20is%20cheaper%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20less%20labor-intensive%20than%20slabbing.%20It's%20basically%20a%20marshmallow%20printer%2C%20and%20it's%20why%20American%20marshmallows%20are%20so%20ubiquitous.%20But%20when%20Hoj%20went%20to%20visit%20Doumak%2C%20the%20company%20in%20suburban%20Chicago%20that%20pioneered%20marshmallow%20extrusion%2C%20the%20experts%20just%20shook%20their%20heads.%20%26quot%3BWe%20love%20your%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20told%20Hoj.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20too%20complex%20for%20our%20system.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223427%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20picking%20up%20a%20melting%20smashmallow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c15bc243bb77284ba3cc9a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222467%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELiam%20Eisenberg%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20colors%20and%20flavors%20Smashmallow%20was%20using%20were%20too%20thick%20for%20Doumak's%20mixers.%20The%20tapioca%20syrup%20and%20invert%20sugar%20would%20have%20required%20new%20tanks.%20Oh%2C%20and%20nobody%20had%20ever%20made%20a%20square%20marshmallow%20on%20a%20commercial%20machine%2C%20much%20less%20a%20marshmallow%20that%20wanted%20to%20mimic%20the%20rough-cut%20straight%20edges%20of%20a%20slabbed%20one.%20And%20that%20doesn't%20even%20get%20into%20the%20coatings%20and%20inclusions%2C%20like%20chocolate%20chips.%20Doumak's%20engineers%20told%20the%20would-be%20Wonkas%20that%20it%20couldn't%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%3A%20Nobody%20was%20%3Cem%3Eforcing%3C%2Fem%3E%20Sebastiani%20to%20turn%20Smashmallow%20into%20a%20national%20brand.%20The%20company%20was%20already%20generating%20nearly%20%2415%20million%20a%20year.%20It%20had%20dozens%20of%20employees.%20It%20was%20making%20a%20product%20that%20people%20loved%20and%20wanted%20to%20buy.%20Rather%20than%20trying%20to%20blow%20the%20company%20up%20into%20another%20Krave-size%20winner%2C%20Sebastiani%20could%20have%20just%20%E2%80%A6%20stopped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20have%20been%20a%20boutique%20regional%20brand%2C%26quot%3B%20Sebastiani%20acknowledges.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20there's%20something%20authentic%20and%20noble%20in%20not%20having%20to%20be%20defined%20by%20your%20revenue%2C%20or%20millions%20of%20customers%2C%20or%20the%20retailers%20you%20have.%20But%20for%20me%2C%20I'm%20driven%20by%20growing%20things%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20infinity%2C%20but%20to%20a%20high%20ceiling.%26quot%3B%20He%20didn't%20just%20want%20to%20make%20marshmallows.%20Sebastiani%20wanted%20to%20change%20our%20eating%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Theranos%20taught%20us%20anything%2C%20it's%20that%20a%20business%20model%20won't%20work%20if%20it%20hinges%20on%20a%20technology%20that%20doesn't%20exist.%20Sebastiani%20wasn't%20an%20Elizabeth%20Holmes-style%20grifter.%20Marshmallows%20are%20real!%20But%20he%20did%20ignore%20the%20experts%2C%20and%20proceeded%20without%20having%20the%20necessary%20technology%20in%20place.%20If%20there%20wasn't%20a%20machine%20that%20could%20mass-produce%20his%20marshmallows%2C%20he%20would%20just%20build%20one.%20How%20hard%20could%20it%20be%3F%20In%20Silicon%20Valley%20parlance%2C%20he%20would%20fake%20it%20until%20he%20could%20make%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20Las%20Vegas%20trade%20show%20for%20food-equipment%20suppliers%2C%20Hoj%20saw%20a%20booth%20for%20Tanis%20Food%20Tec.%20Based%20in%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Tanis%20was%20an%20internationally%20respected%20builder%20of%20candymaking%20machines%2C%20and%20it%20specialized%20in%20marshmallows.%20So%20Hoj%20walked%20over%20and%20broke%20open%20a%20bag%20of%20Smashmallows.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20we%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20them.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0It%20wasn't%20the%20kind%20of%20confection%20the%20Tanis%20people%20were%20used%20to%20making%2C%20but%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20give%20it%20a%20shot.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoj%20went%20to%20the%20Netherlands%20to%20see%20the%20Tanis%20facilities.%20The%20company%20even%20mailed%20samples%20of%20marshmallows%20it%20had%20produced%20to%20Smashmallow's%20specs.%20%26quot%3BThose%20met%20all%20the%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20It%20was%20going%20to%20cost%20a%20lot.%20But%20that%20was%20fine%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20even%20good!%20The%20new%20technology%20would%20be%20a%20trade%20secret%20that%20could%20protect%20Smashmallow%20from%20aspiring%20competitors.%20So%20Sebastiani%20agreed%20to%20buy%20a%20brand-new%20system%20from%20Tanis%20for%20%243%20million%2C%20with%20a%20two-year%20exclusive%20on%20the%20unique%2C%20customized%20parts%20used%20for%20adding%20inclusions%20like%20chocolate%20chips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETanis%20put%20Smashmallow%20in%20touch%20with%20a%20copacker%20in%20Pennsylvania%20called%20Wolfgang%20Confectioners%2C%20which%20agreed%20to%20build%20a%20whole%20new%20facility%20to%20accommodate%20the%20machine.%20It%20would%20be%20the%20size%20of%20two%20tennis%20courts%3A%20kitchen%2C%20mixers%20and%20aerators%2C%20heating%20system%2C%20extruder%2C%20and%20100%20feet%20of%20conveyor%20belts.%20But%20copackers%20hate%20new%20machines.%20They're%20expensive%20to%20install%20and%20maintain%2C%20and%20they're%20basically%20useless%20if%20the%20company%20using%20them%20fails.%20So%20Wolfgang's%20facility%20came%20with%20a%20condition.%20%26quot%3BWe%20needed%20to%20make%201%2C200%20to%202%2C000%20pounds%20an%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20A%20ton%20of%20marshmallows%20every%20hour%2C%20all%20day%20long%20%E2%80%94%20otherwise%20Smashmallow%20would%20be%20required%20to%20pay%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20steel%20machine%2C%20two%20big%20tanks%20and%20lots%20of%20ducts%2C%20in%20an%20all-white%20facility%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b955d043bb77284ba1dce9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20machine%20to%20mass%20produce%20Smashmallows%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20disaster%20%E2%80%94%20and%20never%20made%20enough%20marshmallows.%3Cp%3Ecourtesy%20of%20Jens%20Hoj%2FSmashmallow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESmashmallow%20fired%20the%20teams%20who%20had%20been%20slabbing%20its%20product.%20But%20when%20the%20Tanis%20machine%20finally%20arrived%20at%20the%20Wolfgang%20facility%20in%20August%202019%20and%20Hoj's%20team%20spun%20it%20up%2C%20the%20marshmallow%20printer%20failed%20to%20print.%20%26quot%3BThey%20couldn't%20get%20the%20kitchen%20to%20make%20a%20marshmallow%20for%20quite%20some%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20couldn't%20get%20the%20product%20onto%20the%20belt%20for%20another%202%20%C2%BD%20weeks.%20And%20then%20the%20belt%20wasn't%20functioning%20correctly%2C%20and%20pounds%20per%20hour%20were%20less%20than%20stated.%26quot%3B%20The%20whole%20thing%20was%20a%20disaster%2C%20but%20Hoj%20was%20undeterred.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20thinking%2C%20this%20is%20just%20startup%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20alarming%2C%20the%20coat%20of%20starch%20that%20was%20supposed%20to%20coat%20the%20extruded%20marshmallows%20went%20airborne%2C%20filling%20the%20facility%20with%20starch%20dust.%20Aerosolized%20dust%20isn't%20just%20an%20inconvenience.%20If%20a%20single%20particle%20catches%20fire%2C%20it%20can%20set%20all%20the%20particles%20nearby%20on%20fire%20as%20well%2C%20creating%20a%20rapidly%20expanding%2C%20three-dimensional%20zone%20of%20combustion.%20This%20is%20what's%20known%2C%20in%20technical%20terms%2C%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bexplosion.%26quot%3B%20An%20inspector%2C%20hired%20by%20Wolfgang%2C%20shut%20the%20whole%20thing%20down.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20hesitant%20to%20produce%20product%20until%20it%20was%20fixed%2C%20which%20of%20course%20we%20hated%20hearing%2C%20because%20we%20needed%20the%20pounds%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20To%20get%20up%20and%20running%20again%2C%20Smashmallow%20was%20forced%20to%20bring%20in%20an%20all-new%20dust-handling%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20cascaded%2C%20one%20sugar-coated%20disaster%20after%20another.%20The%20conveyor%20belt%20that%20carried%20individual%20marshmallows%20to%20the%20bagging%20station%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20too%20short%2C%20so%20they%20didn't%20have%20time%20to%20dry%2C%20which%20caused%20the%20marshmallows%20to%20stick%20together%20in%20the%20bag.%20The%20machine's%20die%20and%20cutting%20blade%20couldn't%20replicate%20Smashmallow's%20handmade%20irregularity%3B%20it%20could%20only%20turn%20out%20perfect%2C%20identical-size%20marshmallows.%20When%20the%20machine%20tried%20to%20re-create%20Smashmallow's%20most%20popular%20flavor%2C%20churro%2C%20the%20cinnamon%20coating%20didn't%20stick%20and%20blew%20into%20the%20air.%20Workers%20had%20trouble%20breathing%20through%20the%20thick%20clouds%20of%20spice.%20Once%20they%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20get%20the%20cinnamon%20settled%20onto%20the%20belt%2C%20it%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20heavier%20than%20starch%2C%20and%20the%20motors%20couldn't%20handle%20the%20extra%20weight.%20They%20replaced%20the%20motors%2C%20but%20then%20the%20cut%20ends%20of%20the%20marshmallows%20didn't%20get%20as%20much%20cinnamon%20coating.%20So%20they%20had%20to%20take%20the%20cinnamon%20and%20sugar%20off%20the%20line%20and%20put%20it%20into%20a%20drum%20that%20could%20toss%20the%20marshmallows%20in%20the%20mixture.%20%26quot%3BIt%20took%20about%20six%20or%20seven%20months%20to%20come%20up%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20And%20even%20that%20didn't%20work%2C%20because%20the%20cinnamon%20%E2%80%94%20heavier%20than%20starch%2C%20but%20lighter%20than%20sugar%20%E2%80%94%20prevented%20the%20sugar%20from%20sticking%20to%20the%20marshmallows.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20conveyor%20belt%20with%20workers%20dodging%20from%20flying%20marshmallows%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c15c106fcb546d2d4c613f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223724%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELiam%20Eisenberg%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20COVID%20hit%2C%20slowing%20things%20down%20even%20more.%20The%20production%20line%20wasn't%20fully%20%26quot%3Bcommissioned%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20able%20to%20make%20things%20that%20could%20be%20sold%20%E2%80%94%20until%202021%2C%20nearly%20two%20years%20after%20it%20was%20delivered.%20Even%20then%2C%20Hoj%20says%2C%20it%20didn't%20produce%20the%20amounts%20Wolfgang%20was%20demanding%3A%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20we%20hit%201%2C400%20pounds.%20But%20the%20average%2C%20if%20you%20looked%20at%20a%20whole%20month%2C%20was%20about%20850%20pounds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolfgang's%20quotas%20weren't%20the%20only%20problem.%20The%20sales%20team%20had%20gotten%20Smashmallows%20into%2015%2C000%20stores%2C%20and%20those%20retailers%20were%20signing%20agreements%20for%20product%20up%20to%2018%20months%20in%20advance.%20Sebastiani%20had%20made%20a%20deal%20for%20coveted%20end-aisle%20displays%20for%20Halloween%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BMalloween!%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20every%20Target%20store%20in%20America.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20expecting%20a%20significant%20growth%20curve%2C%26quot%3B%20Sebastiani%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20taking%20on%20investment%20dollars%2C%20not%20only%20from%20my%20firm%2C%20Sonoma%20Capital%2C%20but%20from%20limited%20partners%20and%20endowments.%20My%20reputation%20was%20on%20the%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manufacturing%20team%20started%20hand-tossing%20marshmallows%20in%20the%20cinnamon-sugar%20mix.%20QA%20teams%20inspected%20every%20run%2C%20hoping%20for%20a%20salvageable%20product.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20to%20deliver%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%20But%20customers%20could%20tell%20that%20the%20machine-produced%20marshmallows%20weren't%20as%20good%20as%20the%20originals.%20Sales%20declined.%20Stores%20cut%20back%20on%20their%20orders.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20producing%20four%20days%20a%20week%2C%20and%20then%20we%20were%20down%20to%20three%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoj%20says.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20relationship%20between%20Smashmallow%20and%20Tanis%20finally%20broke.%20Smashmallow%20threatened%20to%20withhold%20payment%20until%20repairs%20were%20made%2C%20and%20canceled%20the%20installation%20of%20the%20experimental%20component%20designed%20to%20improve%20the%20addition%20of%20inclusions.%20Tanis%20responded%20by%20ceasing%20tech%20support.%20An%20acrimonious%20meeting%20aimed%20at%20resolving%20the%20issues%20ended%20with%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20payment%20plan%20tied%20to%20production%20levels.%20If%20Smashmallow%20couldn't%20produce%20enough%20marshmallows%2C%20Tanis%20wouldn't%20get%20its%20dough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20Smashmallow%20couldn't%20keep%20up%20with%20its%20obligations%20to%20investors%2C%20retailers%2C%20and%20the%20copacker.%20Sebastiani's%20dream%20of%20candy%20dominance%20was%20dead.%20Wolfgang%20sued%20to%20recover%20the%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20dollars%20it%20said%20Smashmallow%20owed%20for%20not%20keeping%20up%20with%20sugar%20quotas%3B%20Sebastiani%20settled%20by%20giving%20them%20components%20from%20the%20machine.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHe%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20sued%20Tanis%20to%20recover%20not%20only%20the%20costs%20of%20the%20entire%20fiasco%20but%20the%20potential%20value%20of%20the%20company%2C%20had%20it%20been%20a%20success.%20In%202022%2C%20Smashmallow%20shut%20down%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20Tanis%20insisted%20that%20the%20machine%20had%2C%20at%20times%2C%20gotten%20up%20to%20full%20speed%20and%20satisfied%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20contract.%20It%20accused%20Smashmallow%20of%20slowing%20the%20assembly%20line's%20output%20by%20switching%20up%20the%20flavors%20too%20often%2C%20requiring%20time-consuming%20cleanup.%20But%20at%20trial%2C%20a%20Tanis%20engineer%20admitted%20that%20the%20samples%20Tanis%20had%20sent%20to%20Smashmallow%20to%20prove%20it%20could%20produce%20the%20product%20were%20actually%20made%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20hand.%20Apparently%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETanis%2C%20too%2C%20had%20faked%20it%20to%20make%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20agrees%20that%20it%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20possible%2C%20engineering-wise%2C%20to%20make%20a%20machine%20that%20made%20Smashmallows.%20Everyone%20also%20agrees%20that%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20no%20one%20was%20able%20to.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20Tanis%20said%20they%20could%20do%20it%20was%20interesting%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Richard%20Hartel%2C%20a%20food%20engineer%20who%20leads%20the%20candymaking%20program%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20engineers%20must%20have%20said%2C%20'Well%2C%20this%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20problem.'%20They%20probably%20figured%20this%20was%20going%20to%20be%20easy%2C%20and%20it%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20harder%20than%20they%20thought.%26quot%3B%20The%20jury%20agreed%2C%20awarding%20Smashmallow%20%2420%20million%20in%20damages.%20After%20some%20legal%20back-and-forth%2C%20the%20parties%20settled%20for%20an%20undisclosed%20amount.%20(Tanis%20and%20Wolfgang%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESebastiani%20says%20he%20can%20imagine%20bringing%20Smashmallow%20back%20someday.%20Meanwhile%20his%20investment%20company%20is%20still%20running%20the%20premium-product-at-blitzscale%20playbook.%20Bachan's%20Japanese-style%20barbecue%20sauce%20is%20one%20of%20theirs.%20Guayak%C3%AD%20yerba%20mat%C3%A9%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%2C%20even%20though%20Smashmallow%20failed%2C%20Sebastiani%20didn't.%20During%20trial%20prep%2C%20his%20lawyers%20had%20a%20fun%20idea.%20They%20thought%20they%20might%20bring%20a%20bag%20of%20Smashmallows%20to%20trial%2C%20to%20show%20the%20judge%20and%20jury%20what%20they%20were%20talking%20about.%20One%20of%20the%20attorneys%2C%20David%20Kwasniewski%2C%20called%20a%20bunch%20of%20Bay%20Area%20stores%2C%20and%20a%20clerk%20at%20an%20REI%20in%20Santa%20Rosa%20said%20they%20had%20a%20bag%20in%20stock.%20%26quot%3BCome%20on%20by%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKwasniewski%20hopped%20in%20a%20car%20and%20drove%20up%20from%20San%20Francisco%20%E2%80%94%20it%20takes%20about%20an%20hour.%20He%20walked%20into%20the%20store%20and%20found%20the%20clerk%2C%20who%20went%20behind%20the%20counter%20and%20handed%20him%20a%20bag%20of%20gourmet%20marshmallows.%20But%20they%20weren't%20Smashmallows.%20These%20were%20made%20by%20a%20small%20Colorado%20company%20called%20Hammond's%2C%20which%20sells%20cube-shaped%20premium%20marshmallows%20in%20toasted%20coconut%2C%20chocolate%20chip%2C%20and%20a%20two-layer%20strawberry%20cr%C3%A9me%2C%20among%20other%20flavors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20was%20gobsmacked.%20Smashmallow%20had%20crossed%20over%20into%20that%20rarest%20of%20territories%20%E2%80%94%20a%20brand%20that's%20become%20synonymous%20with%20its%20product.%20%26quot%3BIn%20that%20industry%2C%20a%20snackable%20marshmallow%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20Smashmallow%2C%20like%20a%20copy%20machine%20is%20a%20Xerox%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kwasniewski.%20Smashmallows%20don't%20exist%20anymore%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20brand%20is%20still%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESebastiani%20really%20did%20disrupt%20people's%20usage%20occasions.%20He%20created%20a%20whole%20new%20category%20of%20snack%2C%20and%20changed%20people's%20eating%20habits.%20When%20he%20created%20Smashmallow%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fortunebusinessinsights.com%2Fnorth-america-marshmallow-market-105434%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eannual%20market%20for%20marshmallows%20in%20North%20America%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20about%20%24250%20million.%20By%202028%2C%20it's%20projected%20to%20hit%20%24535%20million.%20Sebastiani%20won't%20see%20a%20dime%20of%20that%20money%2C%20because%20his%20business%20plan%20required%20a%20technology%20that%20didn't%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20couldn't%20%E2%80%94%20exist.%20He%20built%20a%20sweet%20brand.%20But%20the%20product%20was%20mostly%20hot%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20h