0would%20block%20car%20doors%20or%20shout%20through%20megaphones.%20Designated%20%26quot%3Bsidewalk%20counselors%26quot%3B%20wove%20in%20front%20of%20patients%2C%20trying%20to%20convince%20them%20not%20to%20enter%20the%20clinic.%20In%20a%20neighborhood%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prri.org%2Fspotlight%2Freligion-new-york-citys-five-boroughs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20high%20Catholic%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20patients%20might%20see%20a%20priest%20or%20members%20of%20their%20congregation%20telling%20them%20they%20were%20committing%20a%20sin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20clinic%20escorts%20always%20came%20back%2C%20guiding%20patients%20to%20the%20door.%20In%20the%20freezing%20darkness%20of%20winter%2C%20the%20pouring%20rain%20of%20spring%2C%20and%20the%20sweltering%20heat%20of%20summer%2C%20they%20waited%20until%20the%20last%20protestor%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20out%20there%20to%20ensure%20that%20somebody%20who%20is%20facing%20judgment%20as%20they%20enter%20an%20abortion%20clinic%20also%20receives%20support%20and%20kindness%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chelsea%2C%20who%20began%20volunteering%20as%20a%20clinic%20escort%20at%20Bronx%20Abortion%20in%202017.%20(She%20asked%20to%20be%20identified%20only%20by%20her%20first%20name%2C%20citing%20safety%20concerns.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBronx%20Abortion%20was%20established%20in%201969%2C%20around%20the%20time%20New%20York%20State%20legalized%20the%20procedure.%20The%20red%20stucco%20corner%20building%20on%20Eastchester%20Road%20became%20a%20place%20people%20could%20go%20for%20safe%20abortions%20even%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%201973%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManaged%20by%20a%20small%20staff%2C%20the%20independent%20clinic%20provided%20between%20one%20and%20two%20thousand%20abortions%20per%20year%20to%20mostly%20Black%20and%20Latinx%20patients.%20Clinic%20escorts%20said%20it%20was%20deeply%20loved%20by%20those%20who%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20pillar%20of%20reproductive%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20decades%2C%20employees%20came%20and%20went.%20Laws%20changed.%20But%20the%20clinic%20never%20stopped%20providing%20abortions%20to%20the%20patients%20who%20arrived%20at%20its%20doors%20%E2%80%94%20until%20last%20year%2C%20when%20one%20woman's%20sudden%20death%20brought%20Bronx%20Abortion%20to%20its%20knees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224404%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abortion%20Clinic%20in%20the%20Bronx%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de55ab6080194819fa9cfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223303%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBronx%20Abortion%20was%20located%20in%20Morris%20Park%20and%20provided%20care%20to%20predominantly%20Black%20and%20Latinx%20patients.%3Cp%3EAllison%20Hess%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Saturdays%2C%20while%20protestors%20and%20clinic%20escorts%20took%20their%20positions%20outside%2C%20a%20petite%20blond%20woman%20in%20her%2080s%20named%20Irene%20Sylvor%20delivered%20steaming%20coffee%20to%20the%20staff%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESylvor's%20official%20title%20was%20clinic%20director.%20In%20reality%2C%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20heart%2C%20soul%2C%20everything%20of%20Bronx%20Abortion%2C%26quot%3B%20Chelsea%20said.%20Born%20and%20raised%20in%20the%20Bronx%2C%20with%20a%20thick%20New%20York%20accent%2C%20Sylvor%20was%20sharp%2C%20funny%2C%20and%20generous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clinic's%20owner%2C%20Moshe%20Hachamovitch%2C%20founded%20Bronx%20Abortion%20while%20he%20was%20a%20trainee%20at%20Albert%20Einstein%20College%20of%20Medicine.%20%26quot%3BWhenever%20I%20went%20to%20the%20emergency%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20cluttered%20with%20patients%20who%20had%20illegal%20abortions%20and%20were%20actually%20dying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20first%20few%20years%2C%20the%20clinic%20saw%20hundreds%20of%20patients.%20Eventually%20it%20grew%2C%20and%20Hachamovitch%20expanded%20and%20established%20abortion%20clinics%20across%20the%20country%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1995%2F03%2F02%2Fnyregion%2Fabortion-clinic-faces-eviction-with-eight-years-left-on-lease.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELong%20Island%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Arizona%20to%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Bronx%20Abortion%20was%20expanding%2C%20Sylvor%20was%20a%20single%20mother%20juggling%20two%20kids%20and%20occasional%20stints%20selling%20art%20supplies.%20She%20cared%20about%20her%20neighborhood%20and%20its%20people.%20Her%20daughter%2C%20Aimee%20Anderson%2C%20remembered%20her%20tipping%20the%20doorman%20and%20superintendent%20of%20their%20building%20in%20the%20Bronx's%20Riverdale%20neighborhood%20generously%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sylvor%20also%20knew%20how%20to%20get%20her%20way.%20Once%2C%20Anderson%20said%2C%20after%20a%20rude%20driver%20cut%20her%20off%2C%20she%20parked%20right%20behind%20his%20car%20and%20blocked%20his%20exit.%20%26quot%3BShe%20did%20that%20kind%20of%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sylvor%20saw%20a%20job%20opening%20at%20Bronx%20Abortion%2C%20she%20applied%20without%20hesitation.%20A%20firm%20believer%20in%20a%20woman's%20right%20to%20choose%2C%20she%20had%20her%20work%20cut%20out%20for%20her.%20When%20Sylvor%20began%20working%20at%20the%20clinic%20about%20four%20decades%20ago%2C%20she%20became%20the%20%26quot%3Borganizer%2C%20the%20leader%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20the%20clinic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Destiney%20Kirby%2C%20a%20clinic%20escort.%20Hachamovitch%20described%20her%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bforce.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20Sarah%20McNeilly%2C%20another%20clinic%20escort%2C%20Sylvor%20took%20on%20a%20workload%20proportional%20to%20multiple%20employees%20%26quot%3Bto%20keep%20the%20lights%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Destiney%20in%20from%20of%20the%20closed%20abortion%20clinic.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de53cdce7f1785b2e453b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDestiney%20Kirby%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20clinic%20escort%20at%20Bronx%20Abortion%2C%20stands%20outside%20the%20now-shuttered%20clinic.%3Cp%3EAllison%20Hess%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EClinic%20escorts%20said%20she%20managed%20to%20knit%20together%20a%20precarious%20system%20of%20staffing%20and%20resources%20to%20continue%20serving%20the%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20was%20like%20this%20little%20bird%20of%20a%20thing%20who%20would%20stand%20up%20to%20the%20biggest%20protester%2C%26quot%3B%20Chelsea%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20she%20spoke%2C%20you%20listened%20to%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20other%20clinics%20that%20offered%20a%20range%20of%20sexual%20health%20services%2C%20Bronx%20Abortion%20only%20provided%20medical%20and%20surgical%20abortions.%20The%20clinic%20advertised%20both%20scheduled%20appointments%20and%20walk-ins.%20A%20patient%20could%20arrive%20unannounced%20at%207%3A30%20am%20on%20a%20Saturday%20and%20be%20out%20before%20noon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20remembered%20a%20small%20space%20that%20was%20often%20packed%20with%20patients.%20Tiffany%20Quiles%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20nearby%20Westchester%20Square%20neighborhood%2C%20said%20she%20accompanied%20her%20friend%20to%20an%20appointment%20at%20Bronx%20Abortion%20in%202018.%20Quiles%20said%20that%20while%20the%20protestors%20outside%20were%20aggressive%2C%20it%20was%20a%20different%20story%20inside.%20The%20space%20was%20clean%20and%20the%20staff%20was%20pleasant%2C%20she%20said.%20It%20was%20like%20any%20doctor's%20office%2C%20a%20space%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20people%20needed%20some%20medical%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20also%20a%20Planned%20Parenthood%20and%20multiple%20hospitals%20in%20the%20Bronx%2C%20they%20come%20with%20certain%20obstacles%20to%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224524%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jacobi%20Medical%20Center%20facade.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de55d290413ab8e1d743f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223393%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBronx%20Abortion%20was%20located%20near%20a%20handful%20of%20local%20hospitals%20and%20a%20police%20precinct.%3Cp%3EAllison%20Hess%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKirby%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20medical%20student%20in%20the%20Montefiore%20Hospital%20system%2C%20said%20that%20many%20people%20seeking%20abortions%20are%20not%20yet%20registered%20patients%20in%20the%20hospital%20system.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20call%20and%20try%20to%20make%20an%20appointment%20for%20a%20new%20provider%2C%20you%20have%20to%20wait%20around%20six%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20you're%20thinking%20about%20abortion%20care%2C%20you%20can't%20wait%20six%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCost%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20prohibitive%20factor%20to%20access%20abortion%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Elizabeth%20Estrada%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Field%20and%20Advocacy%20Manager%20at%20the%20National%20Latina%20Institute%20for%20Reproductive%20Justice.%20In%20a%20borough%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffurmancenter.org%2Fneighborhoods%2Fview%2Fthe-bronx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20poverty%20rate%20is%20around%2025%25%20and%20the%20median%20annual%20household%20income%20is%20around%20%2445%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20procedure%20that%20could%20cost%20up%20to%20%24%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpregnancyhelpnyc.org%2Fhow-much-does-an-abortion-cost%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%2C800%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20out%20of%20reach.%20While%20insurance%20sometimes%20covers%20abortions%2C%20a%20relatively%20high%20percentage%20of%20residents%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcomptroller.nyc.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F11%2FPoverty-and-Uninsured-Rate-by-Community-District-ACS-2014.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euninsured%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20underinsured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20is%20all%20the%20more%20difficult%20for%20non-English%20speakers%2C%20those%20without%20internet%20access%2C%20those%20who%20are%20unfamiliar%20with%20public%20transportation%20routes%20punctuated%20by%20multiple%20transfers%20and%20at%20risk%20of%20long%20delays%2C%20those%20without%20childcare%2C%20and%20those%20whose%20jobs%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20take%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBronx%20Abortion%20was%20easy%2C%20fast%2C%20and%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clinic%20was%20grounded%20in%20the%20community%20and%20understood%20its%20people%2C%20said%20Chelsea.%20It%20also%20took%20Saturday%20walk-ins%2C%20unlike%20Planned%20Parenthood%20and%20hospitals.%20According%20to%20Hachamovitch%2C%20patients%20who%20could%20not%20afford%20an%20abortion%20did%20not%20have%20to%20pay.%20And%20patients%20could%20always%20reach%20out%20with%20questions%20and%20concerns%20to%20Sylvor.%20Anderson%20said%20her%20mother%20always%20had%20her%20phone%20and%20notepad%20beside%20her%2C%20even%20during%20Christmas%20and%20Thanksgiving.%20She%20took%20calls%20from%20patients%20at%20any%20hour%20of%20the%20night%2C%20scribbling%20down%20notes%20in%20messy%20handwriting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20this%20deeply%20rooted%20communal%20space%20that%20people%20trusted%20and%20respected%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chelsea.%20Staff%20members%20were%20usually%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20the%20same%20neighborhoods%20that%20patients%20were%20coming%20from.%20They%20chatted%20with%20patients%20to%20make%20them%20feel%20comfortable.%20Irene%20tried%20to%20keep%20the%20atmosphere%20bubbly%20and%20uplifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChelsea%20believes%20that%20patients%20felt%20more%20comfortable%20going%20to%20a%20place%20they%20had%20driven%20or%20walked%20past.%20They%20knew%20what%20to%20expect%2C%20even%20if%20there%20were%20protestors%20outside.%20If%20patients%20had%20to%20travel%20to%20a%20new%20clinic%20far%20away%2C%20the%20unknown%20territory%20presented%20yet%20another%20layer%20of%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20say%20that%20independent%20clinics%20%E2%80%94%20in%202022%2C%20Bronx%20Abortion%20was%20one%20of%20two%20in%20a%20borough%20of%20about%201.4%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20are%20essential%20to%20providing%20abortion%20care.%20They%20offer%20an%20outsize%20share%20of%20abortion%20services%20across%20the%20country.%20Even%20though%20they%20represent%20only%20a%20quarter%20of%20facilities%20providing%20abortion%20care%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabortioncarenetwork.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2FCommunitiesNeedClinics-2020.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20provide%20nearly%20two%20thirds%20of%20procedures%20nationwide%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20in%20New%20York%2C%20a%20state%20that%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ny.gov%2Fabortion-new-york-state-know-your-rights%2Fprotecting-strengthening-abortion-rights%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommitted%20to%20protecting%20and%20supporting%20abortion%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20independent%20clinics%20are%20at%20risk.%20Since%202015%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkeepourclinics.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20third%20of%20the%20independent%20clinics%20in%20the%20country%20have%20closed%20their%20doors%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20the%20Abortion%20Care%20Network%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabortioncarenetwork.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2FCommunitiesNeedClinics-2020.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bthreats%20to%20these%20clinics%20are%20a%20threat%20to%20abortion%20access%20overall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20risk%20is%20financial.%20Clinics%20that%20exclusively%20provide%20abortion%20care%20often%20struggle%20to%20stay%20afloat.%20Although%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.plannedparenthoodaction.org%2Fissues%2Fhealth-care-equity%2Ftitle-x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETitle%20X%20federal%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20designated%20to%20provide%20affordable%20reproductive%20healthcare%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FIF%2FIF12167%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Hyde%2520Amendment%252C%2520according%2520to%2Care%2520not%2520obligated%2520to%2520cover.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHyde%20Amendment%3C%2Fa%3E%20bars%20the%20use%20of%20federal%20funds%20for%20abortion%20care.%20Desiree%20Caro%2C%20a%20Title%20X%20Coordinator%20at%20the%20non-profit%20organization%20Public%20Health%20Solutions%2C%20said%20she%20tried%20to%20find%20additional%20financial%20support%20for%20Bronx%20Abortion%20over%20the%20years.%20Federal%20laws%2C%20she%20said%2C%20made%20it%20practically%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225238%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cation%20tape%20around%20clinic%20facade.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de5442ce7f1785b2e45400%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223492%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWith%20the%20closure%20of%20Bronx%20Abortion%2C%20a%20borough%20of%20about%201.4%20million%20people%20now%20has%20another%20barrier%20to%20care.%20%3Cp%3EAllison%20Hess%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20January%207%2C%202023%2C%20clinic%20escorts%20showed%20up%20in%20front%20of%20Bronx%20Abortion%20for%20their%20usual%20Saturday%20morning%20shifts%2C%20only%20to%20find%20the%20doors%20locked.%20This%20had%20never%20happened%20before.%20The%20volunteers%20had%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20Sylvor%2C%20and%20she%20always%20told%20them%20in%20advance%20about%20schedule%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConfused%2C%20they%20waited%20in%20the%20cold%20in%20their%20bright%20rainbow%20vests.%20Patients%20walked%20up.%20Volunteers%20reluctantly%20told%20them%20that%20they%20needed%20to%20find%20somewhere%20else%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20later%2C%20Chelsea%20learned%20that%20Sylvor%20had%20died%20suddenly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%2C%20Sylvor's%20daughter%2C%20said%20her%20mother%20was%20taking%20patient%20calls%20until%20two%20days%20before%20she%20died%20of%20pulmonary%20disease%20on%20January%208.%20%26quot%3BNo%20matter%20what%20was%20going%20on%20in%20her%20personal%20life%2C%20she%20didn't%20let%20that%20stop%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bronx%20Abortion%20community%20was%20devastated.%20Anderson%20called%20the%20two%20women%20who%20worked%20in%20administration%20in%20the%20clinic%20with%20her%20mother%20to%20share%20the%20news.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20both%20screaming%20hysterically%20in%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20horrible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBronx%20Abortion%20immediately%20paused%20all%20operations.%20Clinic%20escorts%20kept%20coming%20back%20for%20the%20next%20several%20Saturdays%2C%20waking%20up%20early%20and%20braving%20the%20cold%20to%20make%20sure%20people%20showing%20up%20for%20care%20were%20not%20left%20alone%20without%20explanation.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20turning%20away%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kirby.%20Some%20patients%20were%20angry.%20Others%20were%20scared.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20so%20emotionally%20taxing%20to%20see%20these%20patients%20come%20in%20to%20get%20an%20abortion%20and%20we%20had%20to%20tell%20them%20'we%20can't%20provide%20that%20for%20you%20today%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22923%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Irene%20Sylvor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e20836ce7f1785b2e560be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221178%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIrene%20Sylvor%20and%20her%20daughter%20Aimee%20Anderson.%20%3Cp%3EAimee%20Anderson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20loss%20of%20its%20director%20would%20prove%20fatal%20to%20the%20clinic%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Sylvor's%20death%2C%20no%20one%20knew%20what%20would%20happen.%20In%20his%2080s%2C%20Hachamovitch%20was%20ready%20to%20retire%20and%20expressed%20interest%20in%20selling%20to%20another%20clinic.%20But%20after%20one%20clinic%20conducted%20an%20appraisal%2C%20its%20owners%20said%20it%20would%20cost%20too%20much.%20They%20backed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20this%20feeling%20of%20betrayal%2C%20but%20also%20I%20wasn't%20shocked%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kirby%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20repeated%20divestment%20of%20healthcare%20providers%20from%20low-income%20communities%20in%20boroughs%20like%20the%20Bronx.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20a%20very%20marginalized%2C%20oppressed%20community%20that%20is%20unfortunately%20not%20going%20to%20bring%20%5Bhealthcare%20providers%5D%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20There's%20really%20no%20buy-in%20from%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Hachamovitch%20sold%20the%20property%20to%20commercial%20developers.%20Its%20new%20owners%20said%20they%20plan%20to%20turn%20the%20building%20into%20a%20restaurant%20or%20a%20storefront.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20could%20imagine%20her%20mother's%20reaction%20to%20the%20news.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20she%20would%20be%20heartbroken%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20closure%20%E2%80%94%20its%20website%20calls%20it%20temporary%2C%20but%20Hachamovitch%20and%20clinic%20escorts%20confirmed%20it%20was%20permanent%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Bronx%20is%20left%20with%20only%20one%20independent%20abortion%20clinic%3A%20Dr.%20Emily%20Women's%20Health%20Center%2C%20located%20in%20the%20South%20Bronx.%20The%20protestors%20who%20targeted%20Bronx%20Abortion%20have%20migrated%20to%20the%20sidewalk%20in%20front%20of%20Dr.%20Emily%2C%20joining%20others%20who%20already%20showed%20up%20there%20every%20week.%20Theresa%20Chong%2C%20Dr.%20Emily's%20director%2C%20said%20the%20group%20has%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%20doubled%26quot%3B%20in%20number%20and%20become%20%26quot%3Bmore%20aggressive.%26quot%3B%20(The%20clinic%20escorts%20have%20followed%20as%20well%20to%20help%20patients%20avoid%20them.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224819%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bronx%20abortion%20clinic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de4f9a90413ab8e1d73fe3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223614%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BEven%20in%20places%20that%20we%20think%20are%20safe%20havens%20for%20abortion%2C%20we%20can't%20take%20for%20granted%20that%20providers%20are%20secure%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chelsea.%3Cp%3EAllison%20Hess%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20borough's%20only%20Planned%20Parenthood%20can%20have%20long%20wait%20times.%20It%20takes%20about%20an%20hour%20to%20travel%20there%20or%20to%20Dr.%20Emily%20on%20public%20transportation%20from%20where%20Bronx%20Abortion%20once%20was.%20From%20neighborhoods%20further%20north%2C%20the%20time%20increases%20to%20upwards%20of%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELonger%20travel%20times%20and%20wait%20times%20can%20delay%20the%20termination%20of%20an%20unwanted%20pregnancy%2C%20making%20it%20more%20expensive%20after%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20weeks%20and%20causing%20emotional%20distress%20to%20the%20pregnant%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20particularly%20states%20that%20ban%20abortion%20altogether%2C%20pregnant%20people%20must%20travel%20hundreds%20of%20miles%20for%20access.%20New%20York's%20landscape%20can%20seem%20comparatively%20rosy.%20But%20difficulties%20of%20any%20kind%20can%20mean%20the%20difference%20between%20receiving%20abortion%20care%20and%20carrying%20an%20unwanted%20pregnancy%20to%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20see%20New%20York%20City%20as%20a%20safe%20haven%20for%20abortion%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kirby.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20the%20truth%20because%20it%20doesn't%20go%20into%20the%20details%20of%20what%20access%20really%20looks%20like.%26quot%3B%20As%20access%20to%20abortion%20diminishes%20across%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%2C%20abortion%20providers%20in%20New%20York%20City%20are%20even%20more%20overburdened%20trying%20to%20serve%20every%20patient%2C%20whether%20they're%20coming%20from%20one%20or%20several%20hundred%20miles%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20Estrada%20said%20she%20has%20recently%20seen%20the%20cost%20of%20abortion%20rise%20and%20the%20wait%20times%20grow.%20People%20have%20to%20leave%20the%20borough%20or%20even%20the%20city%20to%20get%20timely%20care%2C%20and%20some%20people%20are%20unable%20to%20do%20so.%20And%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F13%2Fus%2Fsupreme-court-abortion-pill.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooming%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20about%20access%20to%20mifepristone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pill%20commonly%20used%20for%20medication%20abortions%2C%20that%20care%20may%20become%20still%20further%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20long%20term%20impacts%20are%20innumerable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Caro%2C%20of%20the%20closing%20of%20Bronx%20Abortion.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20folks%20going%20into%20deeper%20levels%20of%20poverty%20than%20they%20already%20are%20in.%20And%20the%20cycle%20continues%20from%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bronx%20abortion%20clinic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de523590413ab8e1d7421e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22778%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20building%20that%20once%20housed%20Bronx%20Abortion.%3Cp%3EAllison%20Hess%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20building%20that%20once%20housed%20Bronx%20Abortion%20stands%20empty.%20A%20forest%20green%20awning%20hangs%20off%20the%20side%20of%20the%20building.%20Dark%20water%20stains%20decorate%20the%20walls.%20Discolored%20bal