20but%20a%20lifelong%20antisemite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanel's%20antisemitism%20was%20'noxious%20and%20notorious'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201883%2C%20Chanel%20spent%20her%20adolescence%20in%20Catholic-run%20convents%20and%20boarding%20schools%20after%20her%20mother%20died%20when%20she%20was%2011.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20these%20formative%20years%2C%20Chanel%20was%20exposed%20to%20rampant%20antisemitism%2C%20Vaughan%20theorizes%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fguides.loc.gov%2Fchronicling-america-dreyfus-affair%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDreyfus%20affair%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201894%20that%20divided%20French%20politics%20for%20a%20generation.%20The%20scandal%20involved%20a%20Jewish-French%20artillery%20officer%20named%20Alfred%20Dreyfus%2C%20who%20was%20wrongly%20convicted%20of%20treason.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChanel%20could%20not%20have%20escaped%20the%20Catholic%20Church's%20propaganda%20campaign%20against%20the%20Jewish%20officer%20Dreyfus%2C%26quot%3B%20Vaughan%20writes%2C%20adding%20that%20later%20in%20life%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20namesake%20of%20the%20Chanel%20brand's%20%26quot%3Bfear%20and%20hatred%20for%20Jews%20was%20noxious%20and%20notorious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222686%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coco%20Chanel%2C%20photographed%20in%201929.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1fd1e90413ab8e1d8446c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222015%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoco%20Chanel%2C%20photographed%20in%201929.%3Cp%3EHulton-Deutsch%20Collection%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20World%20War%20II%20broke%20out%20in%201939%2C%20Chanel%20closed%20her%20couture%20house%2C%20which%20many%20interpreted%20was%20for%20patriotic%20reasons.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20was%20living%20in%20the%20Hotel%20Ritz%2C%20which%20was%20seized%20by%20the%20German%20military%20in%201940%20when%20the%20Nazi%20occupation%20of%20Paris%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20while%20the%20hotel%20was%20used%20as%20a%20Nazi%20headquarters%20that%20Chanel%20began%20a%20relationship%20with%20Baron%20Hans%20G%C3%BCnther%20Von%20Dincklage%2C%20a%20German-British%20aristocrat%20working%20in%20the%20German%20embassy%20with%20links%20to%20the%20Nazi%20military%20intelligence%20organization%2C%20the%20Abwehr.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20early%20years%20of%20World%20War%20II%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%20Chanel's%20love%20affair%20with%20the%20high-ranking%20intelligence%20officer%20proved%20beneficial%3B%20through%20Von%20Dincklage%2C%20nicknamed%20Spatz%20%E2%80%94%20German%20for%20sparrow%20%E2%80%94%20she%20rubbed%20shoulders%20with%20senior-ranking%20Nazi%20officials%20and%20was%20able%20to%20secure%20the%20release%20of%20her%20nephew%20and%20heir%2C%20Andr%C3%A9%20Palasse%2C%20who%20was%20a%20prisoner-of-war%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221950%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coco%20Chanel%2C%20photographed%20in%201944%20in%20Paris.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1fc5d6080194819fb9c4b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222581%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoco%20Chanel%2C%20photographed%20in%201944%20in%20Paris.%3Cp%3EAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20leaned%20on%20her%20Nazi%20associates%20to%20help%20her%20wrangle%20back%20her%20perfume%20company%20which%20she%20had%20sold%20to%20her%20Jewish%20business%20partners%2C%20Pierre%20and%20Paul%20Wertheimer%2C%20in%201924.%20She%20petitioned%20German%20officials%20to%20invoke%20newly%20established%20Nazi%20legislation%20that%20forbade%20Jewish%20people%20from%20owning%20property%20and%20business%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Chanel%20didn't%20realize%20was%20that%20the%20Wertheimers%2C%20anticipating%20the%20forthcoming%20mandates%20against%20Jewish%20people%2C%20had%20temporarily%20given%20a%20Christian%20French%20businessman%20ownership%20of%20Parfums%20Chanel.%20He%20returned%20the%20business%20to%20them%20after%20the%20war%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChanel%20was%20the%20consummate%20opportunist%20who%20was%20going%20to%20get%20what%20she%20wanted%2C%26quot%3B%20Vaughan%20writes%20of%20the%20designer.%20%26quot%3BShe%20knew%20exactly%20what%20she%20was%20doing.%20She%20didn't%20see%20any%20harm%20in%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Chanel's%20entanglement%20with%20the%20Nazis%20came%20at%20a%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOperation%20Modelhut%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221312%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Britain's%20Chancellor%20of%20the%20Exchequer%20Winston%20Churchill%20enjoys%20a%20few%20days'%20boar%20hunting%20with%20his%20son%20Randolph%20and%20Coco%20Chanel%20in%20the%20forests%20near%20Dieppe.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1fbf26080194819fb9bb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221033%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoco%20Chanel%20and%20Winston%20Churchill%2C%20photographed%20boar%20hunting%20together%20in%201928.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20exchange%20for%20the%20release%20of%20her%20nephew%20and%20their%20attempts%20to%20seize%20control%20of%20her%20company%2C%20Chanel%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.spiegel.de%2Feinestages%2Fmodelegende-chanel-a-947864.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%20to%20use%20her%20Allied%20connections%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20the%20Nazi%20cause%20in%201943.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20codename%20%26quot%3BWestminster%26quot%3B%20(possibly%20an%20allusion%20to%20her%20decadelong%20relationship%20with%20the%20Duke%20of%20Westminster)%2C%20Chanel%20was%20tasked%20with%20delivering%20a%20message%20to%20the%20British%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Winston%20Churchill%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20Walter%20Schellenberg%2C%20a%20Nazi%20spy.%20According%20to%20Vaughan%2C%20who%20relied%20on%20contemporary%20intelligence%20documents%2C%20Schellenberg%20wanted%20the%20SS%20to%20%26quot%3Bbroker%20a%20separate%20peace%20deal%20with%20Britain%26quot%3B%20without%20the%20F%C3%BChrer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%2C%20named%20%26quot%3BModelhut%2C%26quot%3B%20saw%20Chanel%20travel%20to%20neutral%20Madrid%20accompanied%20by%20Vera%20Bate%20Lombardi%2C%20who%20was%20to%20act%20as%20an%20intermediary%20and%20pass%20over%20a%20letter%20written%20by%20Chanel%20to%20Churchill.%20It%20fell%20apart%20when%2C%20upon%20arrival%20in%20Madrid%2C%20Lombardi%20%E2%80%94%20who%20had%20been%20duped%20into%20believing%20that%20the%20trip%20was%20intended%20to%20explore%20launching%20Chanel%20couture%20in%20the%20Spanish%20capital%20%E2%80%94%20discovered%20the%20real%20purpose%20and%20denounced%20Chanel%20as%20a%20Nazi%20spy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanel's%20later%20years%20and%20complicated%20legacy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20the%20liberation%20of%20Paris%20in%20August%201944%2C%20Chanel%20was%20arrested%20and%20questioned%20about%20her%20relationship%20with%20the%20Nazis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20any%20evidence%20to%20support%20their%20suspicions%20of%20her%20covert%20espionage%20activities%2C%20she%20was%20freed%20within%20hours%2C%20telling%20her%20grand-niece%20when%20she%20returned%20home%20that%20Churchill%20had%20orchestrated%20her%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201949%2C%20and%20then%20living%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20she%20was%20asked%20to%20appear%20before%20the%20war%20crime%20trial%20of%20a%20former%20associate%2C%20Baron%20Louis%20de%20Vaufreland%2C%20who%20had%20claimed%20that%20she%20had%20been%20involved%20in%20a%20Nazi%20operation.%20She%20again%20denied%20the%20accusations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Vaughan%2C%20after%20that%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20details%20of%20her%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Nazis%20were%20hidden%20for%20years%20in%20French%2C%20German%2C%20Italian%2C%20Soviet%2C%20and%20US%20archives%26quot%3B%20until%20he%20stumbled%20upon%20them%20while%20researching%20the%20life%20of%20a%20man%20who%20the%20Wertheimer%20family%20sent%20to%20Paris%20to%20stop%20Chanel's%20attempts%20to%20reclaim%20control%20of%20Chanel%20No.5%20under%20Aryan%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coco%20Chanel%20photographed%20at%20her%20home%20in%201969.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1fc9a6080194819fb9c8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225610%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoco%20Chanel%20photographed%20at%20her%20home%20in%201969%2C%20two%20years%20before%20she%20died.%3Cp%3EJames%20Andanson%2FSygma%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Vaughan's%20book%20was%20published%20in%202011%2C%20the%20Chanel%20Group%20released%20a%20statement%20acknowledging%20the%20founder's%20wartime%20relationship.%20It%20pointedly%20referred%20to%20Dincklage%20not%20as%20a%20Nazi%20but%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20German%20aristocrat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClearly%20it%20wasn't%20the%20best%20period%20to%20have%20a%20love%20story%20with%20a%20German%2C%20even%20if%20Baron%20von%20Dincklage%20was%20English%20by%20his%20mother%20and%20she%20(Chanel)%20knew%20him%20before%20the%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanel%2C%20who%20died%20in%201971%20at%2087%2C%20continued%20her%20relationship%20with%20Von%20Dincklage%20after%20the%20war%20for%20several%20years.%20In%201954%2C%20she%20reopened%20after%20her%20couture%20house.%20While%20the%20French%20press%20gave%20her%20a%20lukewarm%20welcome%20due%20to%20the%20rumors%20about%20her%20wartime%20associations%2C%20the%20collection%20was%20praised%20worldwide%20and%20she%20cemented%20her%20position%20in%20the%20history%20books%20of%20fashion%20as%20a%20name%20to%20remember.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20first%20five%20episodes%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20New%20Look%26quot%3B%20are%20now%20stre