20a%20similar%20gesture%20will%20be%20extended%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20neighbours%20are%20in%20deep%20freeze%20for%20several%20years%2C%20potential%20efforts%20to%20thaw%20the%20frosty%20ties%20are%20likely%20to%20materialise%20only%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20upcoming%20Indian%20general%20elections%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%98s%20newly%20formed%20government%20on%20Sunday%20elected%20its%20new%20prime%20minister%20following%20general%20elections%20on%20February%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShehbaz%20Sharif%2C%20head%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20and%20younger%20brother%20of%20former%20premier%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20was%20voted%20in%20for%20a%20second%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShehbaz%20Sharif%20is%20declared%20prime%20minister%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%20of%20Pakistan%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20National%20Assembly%20Speaker%2C%20Sardar%20Ayaz%20Sadiq%2C%20as%20saying%20in%20the%20chamber%20after%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharif%20secured%20201%20votes%20in%20the%20336-member%20National%20Assembly%20and%20returns%20to%20the%20position%20he%20held%20up%20until%20August%2C%20when%20parliament%20was%20dissolved%20and%20a%20caretaker%20government%20was%20put%20in%20place%20ahead%20of%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20figures%20would%20roughly%20equate%20to%20support%20from%20parties%20in%20his%20coalition%20plus%20some%20of%20the%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20unelected%20permanent%20members%20or%20potentially%20some%20political%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20session%20took%20place%20amid%20protests%20by%20supporters%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20whose%20PTI%20party%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20run%20in%20the%20elections%2C%20but%20whose%20members%20secured%2093%20seats%20while%20running%20as%20independents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20coalition%20government%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharif%E2%80%99s%20PML-N%20managed%20to%20form%20a%20coalition%20with%20the%20Pakistan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(PPP)%20and%20a%20group%20of%20smaller%20parties%2C%20which%20together%20gave%20them%20enough%20seats%20to%20govern%20in%20a%20parliament%20with%20266%20elected%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PML-N%20won%2075%20seats%20and%20the%20PPP%20claimed%2054.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharif%20is%20the%20PML-N%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20candidate%20for%20prime%20minister%2C%20while%20the%20PPP%20will%20get%20its%20preferred%20choice%20as%20president%20under%20the%20coalition%20accord%20%E2%80%94%20Asif%20Ali%20Zardari%20Bhutto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndependent%20candidates%20backed%20by%20jailed%20leader%20Imran%20Khan%20won%20the%20most%20seats%20of%20any%20party%20grouping%20with%2093%20of%20266%20contestable%20seats%2C%20but%20had%20to%20run%20as%20independents%20with%20the%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20(PTI)%20party%20excluded%20from%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20no%20party%20in%20Pakistan%20came%20close%20to%20the%20134%20seats%20required%20to%20set%20about%20forming%20a%20government%20by%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupporters%20of%20Khan%20have%20held%20protests%20in%20major%20cities%20across%20the%20country%20and%20have%20made%20allegations%20of%20vote%20rigging%20in%20the%20February%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%E2%80%99re%20also%20calling%20for%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20release%2C%20who%20is%20in%20jail%20over%20corruption%20and%20criminal%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709463833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F12115832%2Fshehbaz-sharif.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-shehbaz-sharif-elected-pm-for-second-term%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Let%E2%80%99s%20all%20come%20together%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20and%20the%20National%20Assembly%20should%20pass%2