2Fmodern-myths-of-prehistory%5C%22%3EPart%206.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20takes%20energy%20to%20get%20food%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20you%E2%80%99re%20chasing%20it%20in%20a%20hunt%2C%20climbing%20for%20it%20in%20the%20trees%2C%20digging%20it%20out%20of%20the%20ground%2C%20or%20farming%20it%20and%20trucking%20it%20across%20the%20country.%20Most%20animals%2C%20of%20course%2C%20lack%20trucks%20or%20other%20vehicles%2C%20so%20whatever%20food%20they%20eat%20they%20must%20gather%20on%20foot%20(or%20fin%20or%20wing).%20But%20for%20an%20animal%20in%20balance%20with%20its%20healthy%20home%20environment%2C%20it%20will%20be%20enough.%20Our%20human%20ancestors%20also%20acquired%20enough%20energy%20and%20materials%20from%20gathering%20and%20hunting%20to%20reliably%20reproduce%20at%20a%20slow%20and%20steady%20rate%2C%20make%20their%20tools%20and%20artworks%2C%20dance%20and%20sing%20and%20play%20and%20participate%20in%20other%20essentials%20of%20community%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20287px)%2085vw%2C%20287px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22287%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22394%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20sometimes%20the%20landscape%20provides%20an%20unexpected%20stockpile%20of%20food%2C%20so%20that%20one%20need%20expend%20hardly%20any%20additional%20energy%20to%20gain%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elots%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20more%20of%20it.%20When%20human%20societies%20%E2%80%93%20or%20any%20other%20living%20systems%20%E2%80%93%20gain%20access%20to%20such%20a%20source%2C%20they%20may%20experience%20this%20as%20a%20sudden%20expansion%20in%20the%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20their%20environment%3B%20that%20is%2C%20suddenly%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20effort%20returns%20enough%20energy%20and%20materials%20to%20make%20and%20support%20a%20lot%20more%20of%20them.%20We%20might%20call%20this%20a%20%E2%80%98cheap%E2%80%99%20supply%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%20that%20stimulates%20growth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENotice%20that%20in%20living%20systems%20the%20consumption%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%20are%20linked%3A%20if%20a%20system%20is%20able%20to%20use%20(consume)%20any%20new%20source%20of%20energy%2C%20it%20will%20do%20so%20in%20conjunction%20with%20an%20increased%20usage%20of%20materials%2C%20whether%20that%20material%20is%20the%20food%20itself%20or%20other%20materials%E2%80%94like%20firewood%20or%20coal%20or%20iron%E2%80%94that%20are%20acquired%20by%20expending%20that%20energy.%20Imagine%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20beavers%20living%20along%20a%20river%20encaged%20as%20a%20zoo%20exhibit.%20If%20zookeepers%20leave%20them%20extra%20food%20and%20let%20them%20do%20as%20they%20please%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DIpGwdfX3zms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethey%20will%20become%20more%20beavers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20who%20will%20then%20cut%20down%20more%20trees%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DmDCiW57ljY8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20beavers%20are%20wont%20to%20do%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20then%20build%20larger%20dams%20or%20more%20dams%2C%20increasing%20the%20overall%20size%20and%20complexity%20of%20their%20beaver%20world%20along%20their%20river.%20It%20is%20the%20combination%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%20that%20a%20living%20system%20uses%20to%20grow%20in%20size%2C%20number%2C%20or%20complexity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOr%20consider%20what%20happens%20with%20mice%20and%20locusts%2C%20when%20they%20discover%20food%20concentrated%20on%20human%20farms.%20Mice%20can%20give%20birth%20to%20a%20half-dozen%20new%20babies%20every%20few%20weeks.%20If%20a%20few%20mice%20have%20access%20to%20tons%20of%20food%20stored%20in%20a%20grain%20silo%2C%20their%20population%20will%20grow%20exponentially%2C%20exploding%20over%20a%20few%20months%20into%20%E2%80%98a%20plague%20of%20mice.%E2%80%99%20Something%20like%20this%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F05%2F29%2Fworld%2Faustralia%2Fmouse-plague.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehappens%20periodically%20in%20Australia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20when%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DiFB8ZzOzBYI%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehordes%20of%20mice%20swarm%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20countryside%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.graincentral.com%2Fnews%2Fpowerful-poison-winter-chill-hold-key-to-ending-mouse-plague%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Escouring%20farm%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20after%20farm.%20Locusts%20too%20move%20from%20the%20bounty%20of%20one%20farm%20field%20to%20the%20next%2C%20eating%20and%20reproducing%20and%20growing%20by%20the%20week%20into%20giant%20swarms%20that%20overwhelm%20entire%20regions.%20This%20happened%20in%20eastern%20Africa%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2F2019%25252525E2%2525252580%25252525932022_locust_infestation%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebetween%202019%20and%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20their%20numbers%20swelling%20as%20they%20traveled%20up%20and%20across%20the%20Arabian%20Peninsula%2C%20into%20northern%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20perhaps%20unknown%20to%20the%20mice%20or%20locusts%2C%20the%20grain%20silos%20and%20farm%20fields%20are%20not%20actually%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eunlimited%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20sources%20of%20food.%20What%20had%20felt%20like%20a%20sudden%20expansion%20of%20the%20land%E2%80%99s%20carrying%20capacity%20is%20actually%20merely%20temporary%2C%20illusory.%20The%20booming%20mice%20and%20locust%20populations%20are%20now%20exceeding%20the%20true%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20their%20ecosystem%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esustainable%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20carrying%20capacity%2C%20beyond%20any%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Etemporary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20glut%20of%20food.%20So%20as%20their%20numbers%20shoot%20upward%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20ascending%20a%20ladder%20to%20nowhere%20but%20impending%20disaster%20through%20overpopulation%20and%20environmental%20despoliation%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20suffered%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D6ePv0rkSIiY%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eextreme%20locust%20swarms%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20between%202020-2021%2C%20when%20billions%20of%20locusts%20moved%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Flocust-attack-india-jaipur-climate-change%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eacross%20the%20northwestern%20region%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20decimating%20crops.%20They%20had%20moved%20up%20in%20an%20expanding%20wave%20that%20began%20when%20unusually%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fwildlife-biodiversity%2Fis-india-headed-towards-a-locust-plague-72119%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erainy%20conditions%20in%20eastern%20Africa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20provided%20conditions%20for%20an%20explosion%20in%20the%20population%20of%20grasshoppers.%20At%20very%20high%20densities%2C%20grasshoppers%20become%20locusts%2C%20voracious%20eaters%20and%20breeders%2C%20who%20seek%20out%20farm%20fields%20to%20feed%20their%20exponential%20growth%20trajectory%20%E2%80%93%20until%20they%20crash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20overwhelming%20concentration%20of%20mice%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20can%20produce%20so%20much%20excrement%20and%20masses%20of%20dead%20rodent%20bodies%20that%20the%20land%20can%E2%80%99t%20reabsorb%20it%20all%20quickly%20enough%20through%20natural%20processes%20of%20decay%20and%20renewal.%20If%20they%E2%80%99re%20unable%20to%20leave%20the%20area%2C%20their%20waste%20will%20build%20up%20until%20it%20taints%20the%20ground%20and%20the%20water%20and%20even%20their%20food%20stores.%20Dense%20crowds%20are%20also%20harbours%20for%20disease%2C%20so%20the%20swarm%20can%20become%20afflicted%20by%20its%20own%20epidemics.%20Eventually%2C%20as%20the%20food%20supply%20runs%20down%20from%20having%20been%20a%20surplus%20to%20no%20longer%20being%20adequate%20for%20their%20burgeoning%20population%2C%20they%20begin%20to%20go%20hungry.%20The%20stress%20of%20these%20horrid%20conditions%20can%20also%20make%20the%20mice%20more%20aggressive%2C%20causing%20them%20to%20turn%20on%20each%20other%20and%20fight.%20Their%20population%20peaks%20and%20then%20crashes%2C%20as%20the%20mice%20succumb%20to%20starvation%2C%20disease%2C%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20law%20of%20life%20that%20nothing%20grows%20forever%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20at%20an%20exponential%20rate.%20Due%20to%20the%20inherent%20limits%20in%20how%20quickly%20an%20ecosystem%20can%20reabsorb%20waste%20and%20replenish%20itself%2C%20there%20are%20limits%20to%20growth%3B%20these%20are%20biophysical%20limits%2C%20set%20by%20the%20conditions%20and%20dynamics%20of%20healthy%20ecosystem%20functioning.%20In%20fact%2C%20at%20every%20level%20of%20a%20healthy%20living%20system%20%E2%80%93%20cells%2C%20tissues%2C%20individuals%2C%20populations%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%20limits%20to%20the%20growth%20of%20each%20part%20based%20upon%20the%20whole%20system%E2%80%99s%20dynamic%20stability.%20A%20part%20generally%20grows%20only%20until%20it%20matures%3B%20then%20it%20stops%20growing.%20If%20part%20of%20a%20living%20system%20does%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20not%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20stop%20growing%2C%20we%20recognise%20this%20as%20cancer%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20body%20turned%20malignant%20to%20the%20whole.%20If%20it%20continues%20to%20grow%20without%20restraint%2C%20it%20will%20ultimately%20kill%20its%20host%20body%20and%20thus%20kill%20itself.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20if%20we%20recognise%20the%20human%20economy%20as%20a%20living%20system%2C%20we%20must%20question%20its%20logic%20of%20eternal%20growth.%20The%20human%20economy%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20planetary%20biosphere.%20It%20takes%20resources%20from%20its%20host%20(the%20planet%20and%20its%20biosphere)%20to%20sustain%20itself.%20This%20dynamic%20is%20normal%20for%20living%20systems%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20maintained%20within%20limits%20%E2%80%93%20a%20balance%20of%20give%20and%20take%2C%20as%20I%E2%80%99ve%20discussed%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20previous%20essay%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Yet%2C%20in%20modern%20times%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20done%20whatever%20is%20necessary%20to%20encourage%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eunlimited%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20growth%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20negatively%20impacting%20the%20biosphere.%20Following%20the%20logic%20of%20cancer%20%E2%80%93%20growth%20without%20restraint%20%E2%80%93%20our%20modern%20human%20enterprise%20is%20eating%20its%20own%20life-support%20system%2C%20its%20living%20substrate.%20It%20has%20overshot%20its%20sustainable%20boundaries.%20It%20will%20crash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stockholmresilience.org%2F5.3d04209a18a2642b2fc162a3.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eunmistakably%20apparent%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20today%2C%20with%20our%20mounting%20ecological%20crises%20that%20are%20leading%20to%20mass%20extinction%20and%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20not%20unlike%20the%20organ-systems%20failure%20in%20a%20body%20beset%20with%20cancer.%20But%20this%20general%20trend%20isn%E2%80%99t%20entirely%20new.%20Some%20human%20populations%20in%20particular%20localities%20had%20already%20been%20growing%20too%20big%20too%20fast%20for%20several%20thousands%20of%20years.%20This%20is%20what%20led%20them%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20to%20inhabit%20densely%20populated%20cities%20and%20form%20centralised%20governments%2C%20beginning%20around%20five%20thousand%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03162402%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-4.23.02-1024x592.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03162402%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-4.23.02-1024x592.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03162402%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-4.23.02-300x174.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03162402%2FScreenshot-2024-03-03-at-4.23.02.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699933%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22486%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20mouse%20digs%20into%20a%20heap%20of%20apparently%20contaminated%20grain.%20Photo%3A%20www.graincentral.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Holocene%20presented%20humanity%20with%20the%20first%20prolonged%20period%20of%20stable%20and%20warm%20climate%20conditions%20our%20kind%20had%20ever%20experienced.%20In%20the%20early%20millennia%20of%20this%20climatic%20anomaly%2C%20many%20peoples%20across%20the%20world%20were%20already%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faeon.co%2Fessays%2Frevolutionary-archaeology-reveals-the-deepest-possible-anthropocene%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexperimenting%20with%20plant%20selection%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20They%20did%20this%20simply%20by%20encouraging%20their%20favored%20plants%20to%20grow%20more%20abundantly%20as%20and%20where%20they%20were%20already%20growing%2C%20by%20tending%2C%20managing%2C%20and%20shaping%20their%20local%20ecosystems%2C%20not%20annihilating%20them.%20Some%20people%20planted%20gardens%2C%20favouring%20vegetables%20and%20greens%3B%20but%20after%20a%20season%20or%20two%2C%20they%20allowed%20their%20small%20garden%20plot%20to%20be%20reabsorbed%20back%20into%20its%20ecosystem%2C%20while%20they%20continued%20a%20nomadic%20lifestyle%20and%20later%20grew%20another%20garden%20elsewhere.%20This%20system%2C%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eswidden%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejhum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20cultivation%2C%20avoids%20overtaxing%20any%20particular%20locale%2C%20allowing%20the%20environment%20to%20regularly%20replenish%20its%20integrity%20through%20rewilding.%20Thus%2C%20these%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.currentscience.ac.in%2FVolumes%2F122%2F10%2F1129.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esustainable%20fashions%20of%20food%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20cultivation%20at%20low%20population%20densities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20peoples%20of%20the%20Fertile%20Crescent%20and%20the%20Yangtze%20and%20Yellow%20River%20Valleys%20were%20also%20managing%20their%20local%20ecosystems%20based%20on%20similar%20principles.%20But%20one%20difference%20was%20that%20they%20first%20favoured%20cereal%20grains.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fmodern-myths-of-prehistory%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20nature%20of%20this%20food%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20would%20slowly%20push%20their%20systems%20and%20methods%20away%20from%20holistic%20ecosystem%20management%20toward%20the%20dynamics%20of%20intensifying%20centralisation%2C%20away%20from%20a%20more%20outwardly%20directed%20worldview%20toward%20a%20more%20inwardly%20focused%20one.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20to%20a%20greater%20degree%20than%20other%20types%20of%20foodstuffs%2C%20cereal%20grains%20are%20easy%20to%20harvest%20and%20process%20using%20routinised%2C%20efficient%20methods.%20Suddenly%2C%20a%20lot%20more%20food%20became%20available%20without%20a%20lot%20more%20work.%20And%20based%20on%20this%20easy%20surplus%20of%20food%2C%20their%20populations%20mushroomed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20predictably%2C%20their%20surpluses%20began%20to%20falter%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20their%20growing%20populations.%20Just%20like%20what%20happens%20with%20a%20plague%20of%20mice.%20Compared%20to%20mice%2C%20however%2C%20humans%20didn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20so%20helpless%20in%20the%20face%20of%20their%20mounting%20problems.%20Thanks%20to%20their%20culture%2C%20cooperation%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20imagination%2C%20humans%20have%20a%20much%20greater%20repertoire%20of%20possible%20responses.%20With%20the%20help%20of%20new%20technologies%2C%20humans%20could%20intensify%20their%20efforts%3A%20They%20would%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20keep%20extending%20the%20food%20bonanza%2C%20feeding%20an%20ever%20growing%20number%20of%20bodies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBamboo%20and%20rice%20cultivation%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20regular%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2018%2F04%2Fbamboo-blooms-in-odisha-sanctuary-but-rat-boom-and-crop-damage-need-not-be-a-given%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erat%20plague%20events%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20northeastern%20India.%20Mautam%20(meaning%20%E2%80%98bamboo%20death%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Mizo%20language)%20occurs%20like%20clockwork%20every%2048%20years%2C%20when%20vast%20acreages%20of%20bamboo%20simultaneously%20bloom%20and%20drop%20their%20seeds%2C%20carpeting%20the%20forest%20floor%20with%20literally%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fsrep26135%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etons%20of%20ready%20food%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20rats.%20Within%20weeks%2C%20rat%20populations%20explode%2C%20going%20on%20to%20devour%20the%20maturing%20rice%20crops%20before%20crashing.%20Historically%2C%20this%20cycle%20caused%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fevery-50-years-bamboo-producing-states-of-india-experience-mautam-famine-heres-why-607712.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epredictable%20famines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20across%20the%20region%2C%20twice%20every%20century.%20The%20last%20mautam%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fmagazine%2Fstates%2Fstory%2F20071210-the-flower-of-famine-734644-2007-11-29%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoccurred%20in%202007%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20solutions%20those%20earliest%20farming%20peoples%20devised%20did%20avoid%20immediate%20population%20crash%2C%20but%20also%20led%20to%20different%2C%20negative%20consequences%20within%20their%20communities%2C%20including%20the%20rise%20of%20elite%20classes%20of%20people%20and%20the%20disempowerment%20of%20others.%20This%20enabled%20a%20second%20major%20energy%20transition%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-forged-by-fire%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eafter%20fire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20in%20the%20human%20story%3A%20forced%20labor.%20Low-status%20humans%20and%20animals%20were%20enslaved%20or%20otherwise%20coerced%20or%20ensnared%20into%20expending%20their%20own%20bodily%20energy%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20others.%20And%20much%20like%20the%20mice%2C%20these%20cereal%20grain%20specialists%20probably%20didn%E2%80%99t%20realise%20where%20their%20collective%20actions%20would%20lead%2C%20as%20their%20intensified%20efforts%20were%20more%20deeply%20overtaxing%20and%20despoiling%20the%20land%E2%80%94thereby%20actually%20extending%20their%20degree%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41893-021-00799-z%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20as%20both%20the%20Fertile%20Crescent%20and%20the%20Yellow%20River%20Valley%20were%20being%20over-extracted%2C%20farmers%20were%20spreading%20themselves%20and%20their%20technologies%20further%20across%20the%20landscape%20%E2%80%93%20running%20from%20%E2%80%98silo%E2%80%99%20to%20%E2%80%98silo%E2%80%99%20in%20need%20of%20new%20land%20and%20new%20resources%20to%20make%20up%20for%20what%20they%E2%80%99d%20exhausted.%20Eventually%2C%20some%20would%20discover%20the%20astounding%20energy%20surplus%20stored%20within%20combustible%20fossils%20%E2%80%93%20another%20major%20energy%20transition%20%E2%80%93%20sparking%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution.%20This%20further%20fed%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20human%20enterprise%20by%20making%20all%20resource%20consumption%20%E2%80%93%20from%20food%20to%20wood%20to%20minerals%20%E2%80%93%20faster%20and%20more%20intensive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECombustible%20fossils%20are%20the%20only%20source%20that%20can%20provide%20the%20unprecedented%20rate%20of%20energy%20flows%20that%20underwrites%20the%20human%20enterprise%20today.%20This%20stockpile%20of%20surplus%20energy%20has%20led%20us%20to%20imagine%20we%E2%80%99ve%20liberated%20ourselves%20from%20planetary%20constraints.%20We%E2%80%99re%20lulled%20into%20imagining%20we%E2%80%99ve%20increased%20the%20human%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20the%20planet%2C%20that%20the%20proverbial%20pie%20has%20grown%20larger.%20But%20this%20is%20an%20illusion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20directly%20eat%20fossil%20energy%2C%20we%20can%20expend%20it%20to%20mechanise%20food%20production%2C%20delivering%20more%20food%20to%20more%20people%20with%20less%20direct%20human%20labor.%20We%20also%20expend%20it%20to%20excavate%20and%20deploy%20all%20the%20other%20surplus%20materials%20we%20desire%20in%20order%20to%20grow%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20human%20enterprise%2C%20to%20build%20all%20the%20things%20that%20enable%20our%20increasingly%20layered%20socioeconomic%20hierarchies%20and%20bureaucratically%20structured%20sociopolitical%20worlds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%2C%20not%20only%20has%20the%20sheer%20number%20of%20humans%20massively%20increased%20since%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%2C%20but%20so%20has%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Estuff%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20cosmetics%2C%20clothes%2C%20toys%2C%20gadgets%2C%20houses%2C%20restaurants%2C%20hotels%2C%20cars%2C%20roads%2C%20ships%2C%20shops%2C%20cables%2C%20satellites%2C%20data%20centres%2C%20etc.%20As%20well%20as%20our%20institutions%3A%20banks%2C%20schools%2C%20governments%2C%20militaries%2C%20universities%2C%20research%20labs%2C%20think%20tanks%2C%20corporations%2C%20governmental%20and%20non-governmental%20organisations%2C%20etc.%20We%20might%20think%20of%20all%20those%20physical%20artefacts%20as%20parts%20of%20our%20built%20habitat%20%E2%80%93%20not%20unlike%20beaver%20dams%20or%20beehives%20%E2%80%93%20which%20are%20needed%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20social%20reality%20shaped%20by%20the%20growing%20complexity%20of%20our%20institutional%20systems.%20But%20this%20industrial%20%E2%80%98nest%E2%80%99%20we%E2%80%99re%20building%20has%20grown%20so%20large%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20destroying%20entire%20ecosystems%20and%20displacing%20other%20living%20systems%2C%20including%20alternate%20ways%20of%20human%20thriving.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20economy%20proudly%20boasts%20an%20exponential%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.macrotrends.net%2Fcountries%2FIND%2Findia%2Fgdp-growth-rate%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egrowth%20rate%20of%203-8%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20each%20year%2C%20over%20decades.%20This%20reflects%20rising%20total%20consumption%20driven%20both%20by%20rising%20population%20and%20expanding%20middle-class%20consumption%20patterns.%20Most%20of%20this%20demand%20is%20met%20domestically%2C%20making%20India%E2%80%99s%20rate%20of%20resource%20extraction%20per%20acre%20%E2%80%93%20an%20indication%20of%20pressures%20on%20the%20environment%20%E2%80%93%20among%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.devalt.org%2Fimages%2FL3_ProjectPdfs%2FMaterialconsumptionpatternsinIndiareport.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehighest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Thus%2C%20this%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fenvironment-vs-economy-indias-flawed-logic-that-exposes-it-to-covid-19-like-infections%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egrowth%20comes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20an%20equivalent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2023%2F07%2Finterview-joyeeta-gupta-the-indian-voice-for-environmental-justice-at-global-platforms%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eenvironmental%20cost%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20including%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2022-03-indian-forest-loss-worse-due.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eforest%20cover%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cseindia.org%2Findia-has-lost-90-per-cent-of-the-area-under-its-biodiversity-hotspots-says-cse-s-new-statistical-analysis-10838%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebiodiversity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Funited-nations-report-warns-india-heading-towards-groundwater-depletion-tipping-point-2453719-2023-10-26%2523%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egroundwater%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20attrition%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7795633%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eair%20pollution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2023%2F10%2Fsoil-degradation-in-india-spells-doom-for-millions%2F%2523%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%252520to%252520the%252520National%252520Bureau%2C10%252525%252520is%252520deposited%252520in%252520reservoirs.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esoil%20erosion%20and%20exhaustion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Fvoices%2Fwater-contamination-still-a-serious-national-challenge%2F%2523%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efreshwater%20contamination%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3B%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeer.org%2Fupload%2Feer-2022-249.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esolid%20waste%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20overwhelm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdonellameadows.org%2Fsystems-thinking-book-sale%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESystems%20theory%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20tells%20us%20that%20attaining%20higher%20degrees%20of%20centralising%20complexity%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.resilience.org%2Fstories%2F2023-06-07%2Fthe-collapse-of-complex-societies%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erequires%20more%20energy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20because%20complexity%20%E2%80%93%20as%20instantiated%20in%2C%20for%20example%2C%20our%20multiplying%20social%20and%20economic%20institutions%2C%20our%20nested%20layers%20of%20governance%2C%20the%20tangled%20supply%20chains%20that%20feed%20consumerism%2C%20our%20modes%20of%20warfare%20%E2%80%93%20arises%20in%20opposition%20to%20entropy.%20Or%20to%20put%20it%20plainly%3A%20it%20takes%20more%20work%20(energy)%20to%20build%20and%20operate%20something%20that%20has%20more%20interdependent%20parts%20than%20something%20that%20has%20fewer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20each%20level%20of%20centralising%20complexity%20we%20add%20demands%20an%20increasing%20share%20of%20energy%20invested%20to%20keep%20it%20running%3B%20that%20is%2C%20each%20modicum%20of%20energy%20invested%20gives%20diminishing%20returns.%20Thus%2C%20this%20complexity%20is%20ultimately%20a%20self-limiting%20phenomenon%3B%20how%20far%20it%20succeeds%20depends%20fundamentally%20upon%20the%20amount%20of%20energy%20available%20to%20the%20system.%20History%20bears%20this%20out%2C%20given%20that%20every%20complex%20society%20ever%20built%20has%20peaked%20and%20then%20slumped.%20Industrial%20civilisation%2C%20built%20on%20the%20fossil%20energy%20bonanza%2C%20has%20reached%20a%20level%20of%20centralising%20complexity%20previously%20unattainable.%20But%20this%20energy%20too%20is%20limited%20%E2%80%93%20as%20are%20the%20natural%20resources%20required%20to%20continue%20building%20and%20servicing%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20this%20kind%20of%20complexity%20takes%20resources%20from%20its%20periphery%20to%20feed%20its%20centre%3B%20thus%2C%20any%20growth%20or%20stability%20at%20the%20centre%20is%20maintained%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20periphery%20%E2%80%93%20in%20our%20case%2C%20that%20includes%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20the%20biosphere%2C%20the%20poor%2C%20the%20voiceless%2C%20the%20unseen%20or%20unheeded.%20This%20is%20why%20capitalism%20%E2%80%93%20a%20complexity-increasing%20driver%20of%20our%20system%2C%20devised%20to%20efficiently%20move%20material%20wealth%20from%20the%20peripheries%20to%20the%20core%20%E2%80%93%20ends%20up%20creating%20poverty%20and%20requiring%20violence%20and%20exploitation%20as%20integral%20to%20its%20functioning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20increasing%20use%20of%20surplus%20energy%20and%20associated%20materials%20builds%20and%20maintains%20this%20system%2C%20as%20humans%20grow%20in%20number%20and%20our%20enterprise%20grows%20in%20complexity.%20But%20given%20the%20finite%20size%20of%20our%20planetary%20host%20and%20its%20diminishing%20resources%2C%20the%20present%20system%20is%20nearing%20the%20limits%20of%20its%20growth%20trajectory%20before%20its%20inevitable%20crash.%20Indeed%2C%20for%20a%20highly%20complex%20system%2C%20such%20as%20ours%2C%20by%20the%20time%20the%20destabilisations%20of%20the%20periphery%20are%20being%20felt%20at%20the%20centre%2C%20the%20dynamics%20of%20systemic%20breakdown%20will%20already%20be%20well%20underway.%20And%20we%20are%20today%20already%20at%20a%20point%20where%20we%20can%20see%20those%20damages%20closing%20in%20upon%20the%20centre.%20This%20is%20why%20many%20at%20the%20centre%20have%20finally%20started%20noticing%20the%20problems%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fblog%2Fforests%2Fcop15-montreal-tribals-are-sentinels-of-forest-biodiversity-not-destructors-86507%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndigenous%20groups%20at%20the%20margins%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20been%20warning%20about%20for%20generations%2C%20from%20climate%20change%20to%20biospheric%20collapse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEverything%20is%20connected%20and%20every%20living%20system%20has%20its%20healthy%20operating%20limits.%20If%20we%20exceed%20them%2C%20we%20impair%20the%20system%E2%80%99s%20healthy%20functioning.%20When%20that%20system%20is%20our%20own%20ecosystem%20%E2%80%93%20the%20essential%2C%20biophysical%20basis%20of%20our%20very%20lives%20%E2%80%93%20we%20are%20threatening%20our%20own%20survival.%20New%20technologies%20can%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Etemporarily%20distend%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20limits%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20a%20system%20by%20more%20efficiently%20or%20invisibly%20externalising%20harms%20to%20its%20peripheries.%20But%20they%20cannot%20ultimately%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eremove%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20these%20limits.%20The%20limits%20will%20always%20reassert%20themselves%20as%20those%20harms%20eventually%20ripple%20back%20from%20the%20edges%20toward%20the%20centre%2C%20and%20the%20consequences%20of%20overshoot%20are%20felt%20at%20its%20heart.%20It%E2%80%99s%20imperative%20that%20we%20understand%20there%20are%20real%2C%20hard%20limits%20to%20growth.%20We%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecannot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20continue%20the%20present%20mythology%20of%20unlimited%20growth%20on%20a%20finite%20planet.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20we%20remain%2C%20as%20a%20global%20society%2C%20locked%20into%20the%20paradigm%20of%20growth%20at%20all%20costs%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egrowth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20value%20that%20only%20began%20to%20rise%20with%20the%20Agricultural%20Revolution%2C%20itself.%20Despite%20the%20stories%20we%20tell%20ourselves%20today%20about%20growth%20being%20linked%20to%20human%20ingenuity%20and%20progress%2C%20we%20have%20clearly%20been%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20wrong%20signals%20for%20systemic%20health%20and%20wellbeing.%20Perhaps%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20case%20to%20be%20made%20that%20human%20beings%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fbecoming-human-shaped-by-ice%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elong%20and%20well%20adapted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20fluctuating%20and%20mostly%20frigid%20conditions%20of%20the%20Pleistocene%20ice%20age%20%E2%80%93%20did%20not%20respond%20with%20such%20great%20foresight%20to%20the%20astoundingly%20enriched%20and%20stable%20conditions%20of%20the%20Holocene.%20Or%20the%20subtle%20seductions%20of%20grass%20seeds.%20Or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20not%20where%20these%20two%20things%20co-occurred.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20article%20in%20this%20series%20will%20explore%20in%20more%20detail%20an%20alternate%20telling%20of%20the%20story%20of%20agriculture%20as%20a%20revolution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709463523000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fof-mice-and-men-energy-and-cancer%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20the%20stories%20we%20tell%20ourselves%20today%20about%20growth%20being%20linked%20to%20human%20ingenuity%20and%20progress%2C%20we%20have%20clearly%20been%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20wrong%20signals%20for%20systemic%20health%20and%20wellbeing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fof-mice-and-men-energy-and-cancer%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Moon%20lander%20captures%20Earth's%20'crescent'%20in%20parting%20shot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709462619000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108180184%2Cimgsize-773940.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fodysseus-farewell-us-moon-lander-captures-e