0experienced%20a%20night%20sky%20like%20that%20ever%20after%2C%20layered%20with%20a%20timeless%20story%20in%20a%20voice%20and%20erudition%20as%20rich%20as%20his.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20had%20heard%20two%20folktales%20from%20Ramanujan.%20The%20first%20was%20the%20tale%20of%20%3Cem%3EA%20Story%20and%20a%20Song%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20suppressed%20deep%20inside%20a%20woman%2C%20fighting%20to%20enter%20the%20world%20and%20be%20freed.%20The%20second%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Serpent%20Lover%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20about%20a%20woman%20with%20an%20uncaring%20husband%2C%20a%20man%20constantly%20preoccupied%20by%20his%20mistress.%20She%20receives%20a%20magic%20love%20potion%2C%20but%20ends%20up%20feeding%20it%20to%20a%20snake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fci3.googleusercontent.com%2Fmeips%2FADKq_NZ2t969lrkDVdK-CiLv-hoSZ_owosUofAhQxRyxwTebW2LoGlF72Ai8BtUaMeBt5SBqBHnexItdC1KC2JjCxJpRYh1p_svK-sRXbevRA9KrcF70TomYWTsVu-sMIyKkVLaOs_bRKDv0gecPH7ZkodAou1Ck32gQ7Thz-JVpdsEkB1eD32zLe4PCk1wKm8AkRq_lX1ATPK6BK0pKbbieRh5XJjY8q8Xk9ksNVooVub7e1PBYR0wfSc9g2JrYbFManxYlfHtlAl-Bc9R41UtdkQAIkexO3K0vq3VBAvxx-p_uNbybnQzhpw2s7A%3Ds0-d-e1-ft%23https%3A%2F%2Fsubstackcdn.com%2Fimage%2Ffetch%2Fw_1456%2Cc_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cq_auto%3Agood%2Cfl_progressive%3Asteep%2Fhttps%253A%252F%252Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%252Fpublic%252Fimages%252Fd8b247d8-a791-4fda-a73b-e161a6ef7b13_1456x720.png%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221456%5C%22%20data-bit%3D%5C%22iit%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELeft%3A%20Karnad%20directing%20a%20play%20reading%20with%20students%2C%20photo%20by%20Sanjay%20Iyer.%20Right%3A%20With%20family.%20Photo%3A%20Steve%20Young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20Karnad%20was%20offered%20an%20appointment%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20along%20with%20Fulbright%20funding.%20He%20would%20join%20the%20faculty%20of%20South%20Asian%20Languages%20and%20Civilizations%2C%20where%20A.K.%20Ramanujan%20was%20a%20professor%2C%20and%20get%20a%20break%20from%20acting%20jobs%20and%20the%20film%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20moved%20to%20Chicago%20for%20a%20year.%20Karnad%20was%20overjoyed%20with%20his%20time%20there.%20He%20later%20told%20SPAN%20that%20it%20gave%20him%20%E2%80%9Ctime%20to%20read%20Bharata%E2%80%99s%20Natya%20Sastra%20in%20detail%2C%20to%20clarify%20my%20thoughts%20on%20classical%20Indian%20theater%20and%20poetics%20by%20giving%20a%20course%20on%20the%20subject%20for%20two%20quarters%2C%20spend%20hours%20chatting%20with%20the%20research%20students%20and%20teachers%20such%20as%20Ed%20Dimmock%E2%80%A6%20and%20finally%20spend%20almost%20every%20evening%2C%20for%2010%20months%2C%20at%20home%20with%20my%20family%E2%80%94something%20my%20profession%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20allow%20me%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20taught%20for%20one%20quarter%2C%20and%20with%20the%20encouragement%20of%20the%20department%20chair%2C%20C.M.%20Naim%2C%20he%20spent%20the%20next%20one%20writing%20and%20directing%20a%20new%20play.%20In%20this%20play%2C%20he%20combined%20the%20two%20fables%20that%20had%20already%20captured%20his%20imagination%20and%20dedicated%20it%20to%20Ramanujan%3A%20%E2%80%9Cfriend%2C%20guru%2C%20hero.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENagamandala%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3EPlay%20with%20a%20Cobra%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20premiered%20by%20the%20University%20Theater%20student%20company%20in%20May%201988.%20Karnad%20directed%20it%20himself.%20Working%20with%20students%20in%20Chicago%20was%20a%20vital%20part%20of%20his%20fine-tuning%20the%20script%2C%20he%20later%20said.%20Perhaps%20as%20a%20consequence%2C%20it%20would%20become%20his%20most%20popular%20play%20by%20far%20outside%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fci3.googleusercontent.com%2Fmeips%2FADKq_NbefnAQIsDo1yxORTJcAQjC1ZL1oyczae3-HS-mmgQFkHKvLAyA