0Kala%20Parishad%20in%20Bangalore.%20Mattresses%20were%20hired%20for%20audiences%20to%20be%20seated%20on.%20However%2C%20when%20the%20shows%20went%20full%2C%20we%20even%20had%20people%20sitting%20on%20the%20huge%20trees%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20there%20were%20people%20who%20had%20come%20from%20out%20of%20town%20and%20could%20not%20get%20seats%3B%20so%20we%20did%20an%20extra%20show%20on%20the%20same%20day%20%E2%80%94%20impromptu%2C%20with%20no%20publicity%20%E2%80%94%20which%20also%20ended%20up%20being%20full.%20We%20had%20used%20puppets%20for%20the%20snake%20and%20the%20dog%20which%20were%20handled%20by%20puppeteers%20on%20a%20concealed%20catwalk.%20That%20was%20where%20they%20swung%20the%20lit%20lamps%20from%20%E2%80%94%20which%20had%20to%20have%20mustard%20oil%20so%20they%20would%20not%20go%20off%20in%20the%20wind.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cast%20included%20B.%20Jayashri%2C%20Ramesh%20Bhat%2C%20and%20Shankar%20Nag%20himself.%20It%20was%20scored%20by%20C.%20Ashwath%2C%20with%20a%20spectacular%20song%2C%20%E2%80%9CMaayada%20Manada%20Bhara%E2%80%9D%20written%20by%20Gopal%20Vajpeyi.%20Listen%20to%20a%20rendition%20of%20the%20song%20by%20Pallavi%20MD%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fci3.googleusercontent.com%2Fmeips%2FADKq_NYuodSvGkCiQjEtAD16PM6XTMGkiNh50cdfXioKy-LB37Xr9t-nwTG2daFsVDxA5yoaOseP1bEC1LxlrEcK_N1FXGutjbw3usCWZTWaOmxoPh9CGuhXAal626Jwan4UENl7pw9wdGFIfYu7HafEV3qM-YQyafgtO5a1eNcQJ2eai3Cbh4vX5lJKGSELVZvLC1bjuu1LkJHUlFWyu_hXKuDd9yUnM6m0CS13HUc9OV4yJtOGqLqn4zRwyP72psSqRoN4ZC6oTcZueAAMeg27dCdXz6Q7Dp8usiO6vc9e8rajQ96nOPI81i9exA%3Ds0-d-e1-ft%23https%3A%2F%2Fsubstackcdn.com%2Fimage%2Ffetch%2Fw_1456%2Cc_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cq_auto%3Agood%2Cfl_progressive%3Asteep%2Fhttps%253A%252F%252Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%252Fpublic%252Fimages%252F48aaa770-2fe0-4c7c-9525-9817e5fd82ec_1456x474.png%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221456%5C%22%20data-bit%3D%5C%22iit%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22474%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShankar%20Nag%E2%80%99s%20Nagamandala%20(1989)%2C%20with%20Rani%20played%20by%20Pinty%20Rao%20(left%20and%20centre)%20and%20Arundathi%20Nag%20(right).%20Photo%3A%20Ranga%20Shankara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20Delhi%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20Neelam%20Mansingh%20Chowdhry%20was%20creating%20a%20production%20in%20Punjabi%20that%20she%20would%20breathe%20life%20into%20again%20and%20again%20over%20the%20next%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaga%20Chhaya%20(1990)%20drew%20on%20the%20naqqal%20folk%20tradition%2C%20casting%20a%20mix%20of%20its%20performers%20alongside%20city-based%20actors.%20The%20play%20was%20translated%20by%20the%20eminent%20poet%20Surjit%20Patar%2C%20and%20scored%20by%20BV%20Karanth%2C%20using%20a%20medley%20of%20instruments%20and%20vocals%20unusual%20for%20theatre%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuresh%20Awasthi%2C%20in%20a%20review%20of%20the%20play%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98Naga%20Chhaya%E2%80%99%20represents%20the%20best%20of%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20contemporary%20theatre%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98theatre%20of%20roots%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%A6%20Watching%20%5Bit%5D%20is%20seeing%20a%20segment%20of%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20rich%20traditional%20performance%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20rhythms%2C%20colours%2C%20sounds%2C%20designs%2C%20gestures%20and%20postures.%20It%20is%20like%20reading%20a%20cultural%20document.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20watched%20the%20Company%20production%20at%20Kamani%20Theatre%2C%20and%20he%20loved%20it.%20According%20to%20Neelam%20Mansingh%2C%20he%20wanted%20the%20play%20to%20tour%20around%20Karnataka.%20The%20Punjabi%20language%20show%20%E2%80%9Cended%20up%20performing%20not%20only%20in%20Bangalore%20and%20Mysore%20but%20also%20in%20cities%20like%20Udupi%2C%20Heggodu%20and%20Dharwad%20to%20receptive%20audiences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%202005%2C%20I%20revisited%20the%20play%