the%20right%20plants%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20have%20identified%20the%20climate%20and%20temperature%20trends%20of%20your%20area%2C%20you%20can%20start%20choosing%20the%20right%20set%20of%20plants%20for%20your%20garden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESelect%20plants%20that%20are%20well-adapted%20to%20the%20hot%20and%20humid%20conditions%20of%20Indian%20summers.%20Look%20for%20species%20that%20thrive%20in%20full%20sun%20and%20are%20drought-tolerant%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20bougainvillaea%2C%20hibiscus%2C%20periwinkle%2C%20and%20portulaca.%20Native%20plants%20are%20often%20the%20best%20choice%2C%20as%20they%20have%20evolved%20to%20withstand%20the%20challenges%20of%20the%20local%20climate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%C2%A0%20Mulch%20for%20moisture%20retention%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApply%20a%20thick%20layer%20of%20organic%20mulch%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20shredded%20leaves%2C%20straw%2C%20or%20coconut%20husk%20%E2%80%94%20around%20your%20plants%20to%20help%20retain%20soil%20moisture%20and%20suppress%20weed%20growth.%20Mulching%20also%20helps%20regulate%20soil%20temperature%2C%20keeping%20plant%20roots%20cool%20and%20protected%20from%20the%20heat%20of%20the%20sun.%20Be%20sure%20to%20replenish%20mulch%20as%20needed%20throughout%20the%20summer%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20Of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20botanist%20Aarti%20Mukhani%20highlighted%20the%20importance%20of%20mulching%20to%20prepare%20your%20plants%20for%20summer.%20She%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20most%20important%20for%20your%20garden%E2%80%99s%20health.%20Mulching%20not%20only%20helps%20protect%20plants%20from%20heat%2C%20but%20also%20helps%20control%20weed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Let%20shade%20be%20your%20plant%E2%80%99s%20best%20friend!%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20may%20consider%20yourself%20one%20of%20your%20plants%E2%80%99%20closest%20friends%2C%20their%20true%20ally%20